animal.description:
Meet this handsome fella named Phoenix! He came into the shelter November 10, 2020 as a stray and was never reclaimed so he is now awaiting his forever home! Phoenix is around three years old, current on shots, and excited to have a  person or family to call his own. Just a happy boy who is filled with joy and unconditional love to share seems to get along well with most other dogs and is super charming. Would do beat in a home with at least 1 other dog. Went to foster care for about a home and found out he’s a great boy just can escape if left alone outside or if he sees something he wants to go check out. A home with a tall privacy fenced in yard would be ideal for Phoenix.  Maybe you have the most perfect forever home for Phoenix? Stop by the shelter for a visit with him today in adopt him into your heart and home.
If you have another dog and are interested in meeting another potential new furry member please bring him or her to the shelter and meet on neutral ground before adopting. No need to shuffle the animals around any more than necessary. Please know that 1 mosquito bite can create heart worms and they can be fatal if not treated. It is VERY important to keep your pets healthy and protected by keeping them on a once a month heart worm and flea/tick prevention. These animals are counting on you as their owner to provide them with lots a love and the proper health care so PLEASE make sure you are aware and prepared before adopting. Owning a pet is an extra expense and responsibility but is so worth every minute and penny you invest in them. They will add lots of joy and unconditional love if given a fair chance.
The shelter is open Mon.-Fri. 10-1, 2-5 and Sat. 10-4. Adopt a homeless pet and save a life. If you can not adopt right now come out and volunteer and make a difference in the lives of these animals while they await their FOREVER home.

animal.description:
Ron started his life in a dark place. Pulled from a hoarding situation as a young puppy, Ron then spent 7 months growing up in a county animal control facility. We could all learn a lot from him about rising above because that is what Ron does each and every day. 

Under the loving guidance of our shelter staff, Ron has started to explore the world! He is learning how to sit, make eye contact with his handler, and loose leash walk. More importantly, he is learning to play, enjoy his life, and love his people! Now our special, brave boy is ready to head out into the world and find a family to love. 

To be successful, Ron will need a patient, adult-only family willing to commit to positive reinforcement training, a fenced-in backyard, and plenty of love! If you think you might be the one Ron has been waiting for, let us know, and we would be happy to introduce you!

To enable us to hold Ron for a meet and greet with you, a $25.00 deposit will be taken at the time you make an appointment. Your deposit will be credited toward your adoption if you choose to adopt, or refunded after your meet and greet if you decide that this pet is not a good match for you.

animal.description:
Introducing Indie! This precious little 9 month old girl came into rescue in horrible condition at about 6 months old. Her previous owners attempted to treat her skin issues with a chemical of some kind that burned & scarred her back. When that did not work they abandoned her at the shelter. Luckily she came to SCDR & has made an amazing recovery! 

Indie has an absolute amazing personality and loves everyone she meets, 2 and 4 legged. She is housebroken, crate trained and takes treats so gently. If you want a dog ready for Netflix and cuddles, walking or hiking, dog bar buddy, baseball games or outdoor dining Indie is the perfect dog for that. A really playful buddy in the home would be a bonus for a girl like Indie!

Submit your application today at www.southcharlottedogrescue.com!

animal.description:
Handsome, huggable and loveable!  That’s Lennon in a nutshell.  This guy is all about love. 

Lennon lives with a fur sister and a fur brother!  They all get along wonderful and love to play around in the backyard.   Lennon really enjoys the company of other dogs.   Lennon is even cat friendly!  This handsome dude is really getting used to the good life.  He is enjoying the abundance of toys his foster momma has given him.  Lennon has had some small human visitors and has done extremely well with them.  We think he would probably do just fine in a home with kids. 

Lennon’s favorite pastime is sitting in the sunshine with a chew.  Ahh the good life.  He loves his walks and is learning how to walk on a leash and takes redirection from his foster mom quite well.  

Lennon has lots of energy and his sweet, friendly, goofy personality is blooming.  Whoever has the pleasure of adopting this sweet boy will be one lucky family.  

To adopt Lennon, visit rescueapittie.org to fill out an adoption application.

animal.description:
Meet our sweet Henry! What an amazing boy he is, he loves people, loves other dogs and cats.....you name it and I believe that Henry would make friends with it. Henry was brought in from a high kill shelter in Alabama after his owners decided that he was going to get too big for their liking. I'm so glad that the shelter reached out to us, it would have been a shame for Henry not to been here to show everyone how wonderful he thinks they are. We are looking for the right forever home for this great boy to call his very own. If you are interested in Henry or any other dog at NBSR, please click this link to fill out our online adoption application and make sure to tell us who you are interested in.

https://www.newbeginningsrescue.com/adoption-application

New Beginnings Shepherd Rescue is a volunteer based rescue, we work very hard to help as many adoptable GSDs as possible. Most of our dogs come from high kill shelters across the country, so sadly we do not have any background information on them.....but we work very hard to get to know each and every dog brought into our program in need of a new beginning in their lives. We do not take animals with aggression problems (some may not like other dogs, cats, or may require older kids as opposed to younger children, but we will let you know everything that we know) most of these beautiful dogs have been faithful and loving family pets for their entire lives, yet still have lost their homes and families through no fault of their own. If you are interested in opening your heart and home to one of these amazing dogs please fill out our adoption application at https://www.newbeginningsrescue.com/adoption-application and we will get back in touch after we get it processed. If you don't hear from us in 3 days, please send us a gentle reminder and one of us will get right on it.

Please indicate the dog you are interested in meeting, where it says preference on the application! You may also email julie@newbeginningsrescue.com , we are always happy to answer any questions you may have.

If you give them your heart, they will give you theirs.

animal.description:
Meet Cassie, she is approximately 12 months old female GSD who has not had an easy life. She had a problem with her tail, where she chewed half of it off and her would not stop. Her owners let her live like this until they were questioned by neighbors, when then they dumped her in a high kill shelter in Alabama. NBSR was called and asked if we could help her and we could not say no. We took Cassie to our emergency vet where her tail was cleaned up and wrapped to stop her from the chewing. When we got her home, she went to our vet and they recommended amputation, we made the appointment and they took off what was injured. She will turn around and look at her tail now, but will not go after it anymore. Sadly, Cassie is not trustworthy around other dogs, she will go after them. We don't know why she does not like other dogs, but you may be able to find a trainer to help with this, just be aware. She is great with me and is very loving to all of us here and to our 14 year old granddaughter as well. Cassie deserves a loving family of her very own, one who won't throw her away at the first sign of a problem like her first family did. Are you her New Beginning? If you are interested in Cassie or any dog on NBSR, please fill out our online adoption application at https://www.newbeginningsrescue.com/adoption-application

New Beginnings Shepherd Rescue is a volunteer based rescue, we work very hard to help as many adoptable GSDs as possible. Most of our dogs come from high kill shelters across the country, so sadly we do not have any background information on them.....but we work very hard to get to know each and every dog brought into our program in need of a new beginning in their lives. We do not take animals with aggression problems (some may not like other dogs, cats, or may require older kids as opposed to younger children, but we will let you know everything that we know) most of these beautiful dogs have been faithful and loving family pets for their entire lives, yet still have lost their homes and families through no fault of their own. If you are interested in opening your heart and home to one of these amazing dogs please fill out our adoption application at https://www.newbeginningsrescue.com/adoption-application and we will get back in touch after we get it processed. If you don't hear from us in 3 days, please send us a gentle reminder and one of us will get right on it.

Please indicate the dog you are interested in meeting, where it says preference on the application! You may also email julie@newbeginningsrescue.com , we are always happy to answer any questions you may have.

If you give them your heart, they will give you theirs.

animal.description:
Bailey is 8 years old and weighs 70 pounds. She is a truly amazing dog. She is well-mannered, potty-trained, gentle and sweet. She is very loving with humans and even kids -- she would make a WONDERFUL family dog. She really likes to go for car rides and is a great adventure partner. She rarely barks. Sweet Bailey would love to just relax with you and cuddle on the couch or bed and just be with her humans. She is a loyal, affectionate dog. Her owners are relinquishing her because they have to move somewhere Bailey cannot go. She is a really good girl and available for adoption! Her adoption fee is $325 which covers the cost of her spay, all core vaccines (Rabies and Distemper/Parvo), microchip and microchip registration. The first step is completing an application which is available on our website, poochmatch.com, under the adoption tab. Please read the below paragraphs for more information on our process.

If this listing is still posted, we are still accepting applications for him/her. We do not do out-of-state adoptions on highly adoptable dogs; we would only consider out-of-state adoptions for dogs that prove hard-to-place locally. We cannot hold dogs, please submit your application when you are ready to adopt.

UPDATE: ADOPTION EVENTS CANCELLED DUE TO PANDEMIC AND SOCIAL DISTANCING. If you are interested in meeting any Poochmatch dog at our weekly adoption event on Saturdays at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda, CA (5521 Mirage St.) between 1-5 PM, please fill out an application from our website, poochmatch.com, and submit it no later than 11 AM on Fridays. Upon receipt AND approval, the dog you are interested in meeting will be made available to meet on a Saturday. Due to the high volume of dogs and puppies in our foster homes, it is impossible to bring them all every Saturday. The only way to ensure that the dog that you are interested in will be at the adoption event is to FILL OUT AN APPLICATION AND BE APPROVED. Otherwise, we cannot guarantee that the dog you are interested in will be at our adoption event. If you cannot make the time frame of our events, appointments can be made at another time and location solely at the discretion of the foster parent. Please understand that private appointments will be coordinated to meet the convenience of the foster parent/transporter.

All adoption fees cover the mandatory and non-negotiable spay/neuter, rabies, microchip, microchip registration, full sets of core vaccinations (rabies and 1 set of distemper/parvo for adults, 4 for puppies) and deworming. Adoption fees vary based on age, breed, size and the costs incurred on the dog's behalf by us i.e. medical, behavioral training, etc. and they range from $225-$495.


COVID-19 PROCEDURE:
In an effort to create a safe environment for our potential adopters and our staff, we have changed our protocols and procedures during these difficult times. Starting immediately, our procedures will change from what’s written on our website and other social media platforms. Our weekly adoption event at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda is temporarily cancelled due to COVID-19 and social distancing. The only way to meet one of the dogs/puppies we have available for adoption is through completion of our adoption application through our website, poochmatch.com, before 11 AM on Fridays. On Fridays when we review the applications, we will pick the best fit for each dog or puppy applied for and coordinate mutually agreeable appointment times for the applicants who are approved that week. Private appointments are currently only scheduled on Wednesday, Thursday or Saturday of each week. Masks or bandanas are mandatory; faces must be properly covered.

With the overwhelming desire of the public to adopt at this time, we have received as many as 30 applications for one dog in just one week. Working with a staff of volunteers, we are only able to reach out on Fridays to the people we have approved to adopt. If you have not heard from us by Friday, we have selected a different applicant. If you have multiple dogs/puppies that you are interested in, please indicate each dog/puppy of interest on the application at that time so we don’t rule you out for another dog/puppy available for adoption.

Please understand, we have an influx of texts, phone calls and emails that makes it impossible to get to each and every one of you. Not just for adoption interest, but also from veterinarians, people who must relinquish dogs, people who have found a stray dog in need of pick up, etc. We are currently not in need of fosters. Due to the fact that there is such a high demand, we are sticking with strict protocol to not adopt out of Southern California. We apologize for this inconvenience and difficulty to be able to get in touch with us while there is an overwhelming desire and demand to adopt at this time. We appreciate your understanding and patience as we navigate through these difficult times with every intention to keep the public and our staff safe.

animal.description:
Angel came into Lab rescue after being found abandoned in the woods and is completely blind.  She is estimated to be 7 years old.  She had a severe case of heartworms that were treated while in rescue.  She still has a residual cough, but was deemed healthy enough for surgery in September.  At that time she had a mammary gland removed because she had a mast cell tumor (clear margins) and a growth on her chest removed.  Like many of the neglected dogs we get, her teeth are severely worn.  Despite her blindness and medical history, Angel lives up to her name and would make the right family a wonderful pet.


These are some of the qualities she has to offer a family.
- Angel is smart as a whip and can map out her surroundings quickly. Just don't move the furniture around or put something in her path.
- She is a very loving, low key Lab who just wants to be with her person.
- She will let you know if she wants attention by nudging you to pet her or putting her paw on your leg.
- She's not allowed on the furniture in her foster home, but I'm sure she would love that...especially if she could lay her head on her human.
- She takes treats ever so gently.
- She's not a counter surfer and doesn't get into mischief.  
- She knows "careful!", "step up" "step down" "stop", "sit" and "no"
- She's good with other dogs, as long as they don't crowd her. Then, she'll issue a warning or try to get away from the dog.
- She goes on alert when she hears a certain type of bird...ears up, focused attention and ready to head in that direction!
- Fair warning, she snores!

Angel needs a home where someone is home most of the time and she can be the princess. She truly lives up to her name and is the perfect companion.  Angel has had a difficult life but would love an opportunity to be a cherished pet.

---

If you are interested in adopting please go to www.lrrof.org and fill out and application.
 
Thanks so much for your interest in our rescue!
To apply to adopt from Labrador Retriever Rescue of Florida, please visit our website at http://www.lrrof.org. Your support, both through adoption and donation is always essential to us and our Labs. Donate today.
We're about matching the right dog with the right family! All applicants will be assigned an Adoption Counselor who will act as their liaison. In addition, a phone interview, home inspection and vet reference (if applicable) are required for eligibility to adopt from Labrador Retriever Rescue of Florida.

animal.description:
***ADOPTION PENDING***
Luna is a bit of a project in terms of socialization and training so her new owner has to be able to commit to continued work with her. We think she's worth it!! She is a loving, more independent dog and is adapting nicely to having a more traditional home situation.

Luna is a smaller female German Shepherd (21”), about 4-5 years old. She has only 3 legs but is not hindered in any way by this except she has reduced stamina. Once she rests up, she’s ready to go again. She loves to be outside to walk, run, chase bugs, and hang out with you. She spends a great deal of time exploring her environment and entertaining herself when outside but she likes to check in with you to make sure you're still there with her. While she’ll stay outside for a time by herself, she doesn’t enjoy being out for long periods of time alone. As with most German Shepherds, she wants to be where her people are. If you have yard work to do, she will love being out there with you! 

Luna needs continued work related to excitement level as she transitions to a permanent home. Running around outside or working on training with her person or coming back into the house after running around outside can be very stimulating for Luna. She is learning to ‘settle’ and to stay back (so that she’s not invading personal space). She has made tremendous progress in her foster home and has learned to moderate herself when she is in high alert mode. A quick verbal correction is all she needs if she does get over-exuberant. 

Luna has been integrated with a larger German Shepherd and two Australian Shepherds in her foster home. She tends to just hang out, without interacting, most of the time, but occasionally will take up some play with one of the other dogs. When she plays, she can be loud and growly which does not bother the other dogs at all. 

We think she will do best in a home with one other larger dog or in a home where she is the only dog so that she can get the attention she deserves. We believe her confidence level will continue to improve as her daily life becomes more stable. 

Luna enjoys training & she is very treat motivated. She responds extremely well to verbal reminders when a correction is needed. Her new handler has to balance between enforcing the rules and encouraging her. Luna could easily be a dog that learns a dog activity such as tracking, barn hunt or scent work. 

Luna is spayed, microchipped, current on vaccinations, & heartworm tested (negative). Luna came to us with a broken pelvis but that has all healed now and her movement is normal. Please call if you’re interested in talking with us about her.  (505) 877-7352. Adoption fee: Please consider donating an amount of your choice to our rescue.

The type of home I'm looking for:
 I need to be the only pet in the home (no cats, critters, or other dogs)
 Teens and older recommended

These animals are often older or shy, or have medical or behavioral challenges. They still have love to give, and deserve every chance we can offer them. Adopters of these animals choose the adoption fee and can foster-to-adopt to ensure it's a good fit. animal.description:
*****STAR HAS BEEN ADOPTED!!!*****

STAR is a lovely 5 year old sable Sheltie girl who is looking for an experienced Sheltie person/family who is familiar with skittish and nervous dogs.  Star has lived with the same family all her life and takes a while to adjust to new people and surroundings, but is very anxious to bond with someone who will love her forever.  In her foster home, she has declared the man of the house as her favourite so this may be because she prefers males to females....however this may change.  

She is very good with the resident dogs and previously was a playmate to a Pomeranian. Star has also lived with 2 easygoing,  well behaved cats....which she would occasionally chase.

Like most Shelties....Star will alert you to people at the door or any unusual noises which she hears and will bark when she is nervous.
Star has been used to sleeping in a crate and she likes the security of her *den* when she is feeling nervous or unsure.  

An easygoing, well behaved and confident dog would be a good companion for her....in a house without too many comings and goings with people she doesn't know.  She needs the security of a routine and to feel safe in her surroundings.  

Star is being fostered in Niagara on the Lake.

animal.description: Hi there, my name is Rusty. I'm a big teddy bear with lots of love to give! I have a deep bark that might sound intimidating at first, but once you get to know me you'll find that I'm the sweetest boy. My foster momma says I'm very easy going, and sometimes you might even forget I'm there because I'm so well behaved. I love snuggling and getting attention, but I'm also happy to just relax with you. I haven't had a single accident in my foster home either. I love kids, but I might accidentally knock little ones over. When I'm outside, I love to run and play, and I'm still working on my leash manners. I do live in a foster home with another dog. I don't always like to share my "stuff" and can be selective with some of the other dogs I meet, so I would do best in a home with another large, calm dog or without other animals. If you have another dog, a meet-and-greet with them wouldn't be a bad idea before you adopt me. I'm always smiling and happy to greet you when you come home. Hopefully, your home will be my home soon!

animal.description:
She is a stout girl with a huge heart, great snuggles and playful energy. She likes meeting people, great with kids and other dogs, house trained and very well behaved at mealtimes. She shows interest in cats without "prey driven" behavior and we believe she would do well with a cat that is not reactive (running and hissing) and likes the company of dogs. She just wants to play with them but the cat in her foster home is terrified of her and reacts. She is very good on leash, likes to go on adventures and would be a great running/hiking buddy. She recently discovered she can climb over a 4ft gate to go meet the neighbors! She most certainly needs a big yard and doggy buddies to play with. We are installing "Coyote rollers" at the top of our gates to keep her from getting over so please take that into consideration. Meryl will not do well in an apartment and/or without doggy friends. She is a pitty mix and has the most beautiful eyes. Meryl has been waiting almost 3 months in foster care for her furrever family to find her. She is still hopeful.

If you live in an apartment or are renting, your application cannot be considered unless proven that the pitty breed is allowed on the premises.

animal.description:
Meet Ellis!!! He is a smart, attention loving baby! He seems to have a heinz 57 of some breeds mixed in with him (assumed that he is mostly a akita and Lab) and it is evident that he has received some training as he knows to sit, shake and is pretty good with down and leave it. He is super smart, very puppy brained, high energy, wants to play play play, and just needs some firm boundaries set by both animals and human. He is extremely food motivated and is willing to learn for a tasty treat. 

Out of sight is just too far for Ellis and he loves to be at your side at all times. Good luck trying to keep him off your bed! Inches just wont do when this boy wants to cuddle. While he is crate trained, Ellis is still working on being left alone and makes a wonderful telecommute companion (so long as theres lots to do!). Ellis thrives with mental stimulation and likes to work for his food (frozen kongs and Himalayan Cheese are a must). 

Ellis would thrive best in a home with NO children under the age of 13 (and even those at older ages will need to know dogs boundaries, body language and be very respectful). Ellis would do best in a home with a single man, single woman, or couple that would love an adventure buddy! He LOVES the outdoors, but he doesn't like the outdoors if it means being outside all by himself. He thrives with positive human interaction, playing outside, mental stimulation, and the ability to exert his energy. He would reach his max potential as the single dog in the home but is a great dog park dog and loves having friends. He also is quite the talker as well and when feeling silly he is guaranteed to make you laugh!

Ellis cannot go to a novice owner as he needs somebody who is good with training and positive reinforcement. He is currently working on some resource guarding behaviors (toys, kibble, and his tasty chews) but has clear communication through body language. He also needs a home with a fenced in backyard and would not do well in an apartment, condo or townhome. 

Lastly, our professional dog trainer has also volunteered to give Ellis and his new owner a couple of sessions to ensure Ellis is happy and thriving in his new environment! He is SUCH a special, loving, beautiful dog and truly deserves a furever home!

He would not do well in a home with cats... sees them as something to chase and antagonize.

animal.description:
Dapper here! I'm a one-and-a-half-year-old pointer mix ready to find my forever home! Could that be with you? Aside from my adorable freckles and non-stop wagging tail, I am a very good boy, but need to go to an experienced home ready to put in the time to help me flourish. You see, I have a lot of energy and require daily exercise (I love to go on runs with my foster family, however, a long walk or hike will also suffice). After getting my energy out, I calm down nicely and LOVE to cuddle up next to you. Due to my energy level, apartment living will not be suitable for me and a fenced in yard would be best. No cats or young children either due to my high prey drive and excitement level. I will need an experienced owner to help me overcome some anxiousness on leash-I pull and can be dog reactive on leash (excessive barking), however my foster family is working with me on re-direction and I have shown positive progress with treats, "watch me," and the Gentle Leader. This behavior translates in the house when I see a dog walk by outside, I get really excited and bark. Again, my foster family is working on this but I'm a work in progress!
I currently live with my foster family's resident dogs and do great with them, but due to my initial reactiveness, I will need a slow introduction when meeting new dogs. But once I'm comfortable, I love to play and show signs of good etiquette (play bows, "shaking" it off). 
I am an athletic dog that could be great in a variety of "extracurriculars" like agility, lure racing, or flyball. Aside from my leash skills, my foster family says I'm a real catch-I sleep in my crate, I'm housetrained, know commands, and absolutely love my people and want to be with them (or on them-I think I'm a lap dog). If you've owned dogs before and are willing to put in some work with my training and exercise requirements, request to meet me! I promise you I am worth it!

You can also watch for stories, pictures, and videos about Dapper on our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/groups/40103261297/

Adoption fee: $425

Adoption fees for all dogs/puppies include a $50 refundable training deposit. Complete your basic training program and provide a copy of the certificate within 4 months (120 days) of adoption and we will refund $50 of the original adoption fee.

All dogs/puppies have been fully vetted including spay/neuter, micro-chipping, worming, heartworm testing and preventative treatment, flea/tick preventative, and all required age appropriate vaccinations. As required by Wisconsin Act 90, all dogs will have received a veterinarian exam (CVI) within the past 30 days.

Our adoption process requires the submission of an application. Applications and Adoption Rules can be found on our website, on the "HOW TO ADOPT" tab. Upon receipt of the completed application, we will process the application including: contact with your veterinarian and completion of a home visit. Please be sure to include the contact information for your vet as we will call. If your vet requires an information release, please be sure to contact them as soon as you submit your application. We are a group of volunteers with families and jobs, so please be patient and allow a few days for our response.

JR's Pups-N-Stuff Dog Sellers License 270089-DS

animal.description:
This is Lucy- she is a 53 pound Cattle dog mix. She is about 2 years old. She was found stray with her adorable puppies! We took them all in, and now Lucy is looking for a home to call her own. She is doing well with basic manners and potty training. She is doing very well with the other dogs in her foster home. She wants to be near her humans all the time, and is a person dog :) 

She is constantly trying to cuddle with the other dog in her foster home. She has to always be touching her person or the other dog. She is extremely smart and loving! She is our longest foster resident, and is hoping she gets picked for her forever family soon! 

If interested the first step is to send in an application - www.soardogs.org or shoot us over any questions you have! 

Adoption donation required. This covers altering, DAP series vaccinations to date of adoption, Bordetella Vaccination, Rabies vaccination if over four months, Microchip, Deworming, heartworm test (if over 8 months), monthly flea/heartworm prevention to date, grooming, full veterinary examination, and temperament evaluation. Please e-mail us for more information or go to our website https://soardogs.org/adoption-application for an application. Thank you very much! 


All SOAR dogs go through a ten-day quarantine period to ensure they are healthy, before being adopted. We do not operate on a first come first serve basis, but screen applicants in order to find the best fit for our adoptable dogs.

animal.description:
Available for adoption in Texas: meet NELLIE!

Hi, My name is Nellie! Which is very fitting as my foster is always saying “Whoa, Nellie!”

I am a one-year-old and 40 lbs bundle of energy! I have one speed and that is GO GO GO!

My foster home has a dog and a cat. I love to play with the other dog and will play for hours. I have a lot of puppy tendencies and can be very mouthy with my foster dog sibling while playing. I just get excited! I am still learning good play skills but have to be reminded to take a break.

Let’s talk cats, I want to play with them, too! I sometimes try to get my foster cat sibling to play with me by chasing her but she is not interested. I do respect the hisses and growls. If there is a cat in my forever home, they will need to be dog savvy cat.

Now let’s talk toys, I think all things left in my reach are things to play with. I need some guidance on what is appropriate to play with and what is not. I share my toys with the other dog but prefer to be fed separately. 

I love to be outside and sometimes can’t resist an open door. I would love a family that is very active like I am, take me on long runs or walks, and will teach me lots of amazing things.  

I will also need an adult-only family (sorry, kids) with lots of dog experience who will train with me. The awesome news is I am very food motivated and a very fast learner. I already know sit, down, and can almost shake. See how smart I am?

I am fully house trained and I am learning to ring the bell on the back door to let my foster know I need to go outside. I am also crate trained, vaccinated, microchipped, and spayed.

I would love to have a home that will be able to teach me new things, take me on lots of adventures and give me the chance to shine. Is that with you?  

If you are interested in adopting, please go to www.luckylabrescue.com and complete an adoption application.

animal.description:
*Adoption Process starts with an Online Adoption Application you can find at www.adoptaboston.com.  Phone interviews do not take place til after an approved application is on file.

Eligible for the Golden Paws Program (adoptors 60 yrs and older adopting a dog 7 yrs and older get $50 off the adoption fee noted below)

My name is Miley.  I am 9 years old and weigh 28 pounds. My owner passed away.  I am being fostered in Lakewood, CO.

I'm a spoiled princess who has been Queen Bee for all 9 years of my life up until my owner died this summer.  
I'm very sweet and loving, but if I don't want to do something, I won't.  This includes walking on a leash, staying out of the trash, and moving over so my foster mom can get into bed too.  I'm used to getting my way and will give a little sass when I don't.  
I need a home with no small children or other pets.  I am use to being the center of attention.  I have been around other dogs and do fine for short periods.
I've also been overindulged when it comes to treats and table food. I arrived overweight.  I lost weight due to a strict diet. 
I have energy and enjoy walks.  Though I pull on the leash which I need to work on, I like walks which help me burn off energy.  Plus a fenced in yard is a must so I can run free and explore.  
I'm smart but stubborn.  I'm looking for someone who has an infinite amount of patience and can handle a challenge.

Here's a little more about me:
Housetrained? Yes
Leash-trained? Need to work on this as I will pull especially if I see other dogs.
Rides well in car? Yes
Good with other dogs? No
Good with cats? No
Good with young children? No
Good with strangers? Yes
Shy or confident? Confident
Barks? Yes
Apartment qualified? No, I am vocal
Any Special needs or Health Issues? Food allergies. Requires a specific diet (24lbs for $45)
Adoption Fee: $175.00

All our dogs are spayed/neutered (if six months and older), up to date on rabies and distemper, heartworm tested, and microchipped. Other medical needs diagnosed while in foster care are also treated prior to adoption.

MABTR requires a fenced in area from families who own their home, however we DO adopt to apartment complexes and communities where fences are not permitted due to leases and covenants. In these cases a leash law must be enforced.  We do not accept invisible fencing.

MABTR only adopts to families residing in NE, CO, MO, KS, IA, WY, SD, ND, ID, UT, MT, MN, and SW corner of AR due to the lack of volunteer support in other states, no exception even if you are willing to drive.

If you are Interested in Adoption please complete our online adoption application at https://www.adoptaboston.com/adopt/application/. Petfinder's form is NOT our application.  We will respond back to you within 72 hours of receiving your application.

Interested in Donating visit https://www.adoptaboston.com/help/
animal.name: Miley in CO

animal.description:
Dog Name: Yeti
Breed: Mutt (possibly boxer, hound mix, pit mix)
Sex: Male
Age: 3 years
Weight: 65 pounds
Medical Needs: None. Already neutered and UTD on vaccines
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Prefers to be out and about with his people but will settle down in his crate after a few minutes. 
Good in the car: Yes!
Good on a leash: Walks great with a prong, pulls some without it
Energy level: Pretty chill (can go from 0 to 100 in 2 seconds, but also the other way around)
Need a fenced in yard: Hed definitely enjoy it (he likes to do zoomies).
Dog Friendly: Yes, very playful 
If yes, does your foster need another dog in its adoptive homes? Not required
Cat Friendly? No, likes to chase
Kid Friendly: Does great with the 12 and 15-year-old in his foster home. Due to a bite history (no broken skin) we wont place Yeti with younger kids.

Special traits that make your foster special or that we need to know about them?
 
You might recognize Yeti from our #GRReat68. Yeti was adopted 3 times since arriving from JARM about 1 year ago. But, the shoe never quite fit and Yeti was returned. After spending some time with our friends from Delmarva K9, Yeti is ready to meet his furever family furreal this time!

Yeti would do best with an experienced, confident handler.

He loves his family with all of his heart, but has displayed some initial aggression (bit someone without breaking skin) towards an unfamiliar visitor, so a family (or individual) that doesnt get many visitors is ideal for him. He's fine walking past strangers on walks (no barking, lunging etc.) and has been ok with the visitors in his foster home after a short intro/warm-up period.

His foster mom describes him as a "big, happy goofball who is always wagging his tail and wants to be your shadow."

Yeti knows sit, down and come, and is currently working on the place command which will be helpful when having visitors over.

Hes always down for a car ride, walk or some good old zoomies in the backyard and loves to watch out the window (and bark at bunnies in the yard).

If youre interested in meeting him, go to grrde.org and fill out an application.

animal.description:
My name is Ellie May and I’m a 5 year old hound mix. I was rescued from the streets very skinny, scared and heart worm positive by the wonderful people with UnderDog Rescue. My foster mom has been feeding me regular delicious meals and I am looking and feeling much better and I now weigh a healthy 28 pounds.  I am very shy and it takes me a bit to warm up to strangers. I need someone who is patient to help me learn not all people are going to hurt me. I enjoy playing with my foster siblings and am a happy go lucky girl. Once I am comfortable I am a total love bug. I enjoy laying next to you watching tv or reading your favorite book. I am currently under going heart worm treatment at Underdog expense and will need a quite home to recuperate. Won’t you please consider a shy girl like me? I promise you won’t regret it.  My adoption fee if $400. 


All UnderDogs are spayed/neutered, heartworm checked, microchipped, up to date on vaccines and heartworm/flea/tick preventatives.  For consideration for one or more dogs, we require that an on-line application is filled out.  

TO ADOPT THIS DOG PLEASE FILL OUT AN APPLICATION AT https://underdogrescueofflorida.com/. 

Sorry, we do not adopt outside of Florida.  Applicants are subject to a home visit, and veterinary references will be checked. Please include a vet reference (including phone number) when applying online.

Our application process:
FIRST, an application must be approved for adoption from our rescue.
SECOND, we determine whether the dog that has been applied for is a "good match" for the household that wants to adopt him/her.  We take into consideration the dog's activity level, compatibility with other members of the household (human and other pets), etc.
If your application has been approved, but the dog you applied for is no longer available, please take the time and look over our adoptable dogs again.  We will make every effort to find the right dog for an approved applicant.

We hope you agree and understand that our goal to find the best forever home is our #1 priority! Please fill out an Adoption Application at https://underdogrescueofflorida.com/

animal.description:
Have you met Sherman?

10-year-old Sherman was brought into East Valley Shelter LA as a stray, and he became a Frosted Face on October 24, 2020. Sherman is good with other dogs and rotates in several playgroups at FFF. He's such a great hiking buddy, too, as many volunteers can attest to. Sherman is a very popular guy and has been on outings to wineries, coffee shops, pet supply stores, parks, and a pumpkin patch last fall! He is a well-behaved superstar everywhere he goes - even to the groomer!

A volunteer who hikes
with Sherman
shares
, "Sherman is such a gentle, gorgeous dog, and his eyes stare deep into your soul. He was a great hiking buddy. Sherman walks well on a leash - he doesn't pull and wasn't reactive to other dogs. At one point we lost the trail down by the water, and master navigator Sherman used his nose to calmly and authoritatively lead us in the right direction!"

Sherman is
a smart, fun guy who knows how to sit
, enjoys playing
with tennis balls,
and loves snuggles and belly rubs
. He thrives with mental stimulation and physical activity every day, but he also knows how to relax and appreciates a comfy, cozy dog bed.

Think Sherman might be your guy? Stop by an Open House to meet him!

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees and we help with medical costs!

Apply to become a family: https://frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

animal.description:
Parsley's story:

Parsley spent the first 9 months of his life in a cage. Thankfully a nice lady got him out of that situation and did her best to give him a good home. In the end, it was not a good fit for either, and ultimately, we knew we had to give Parsley a second chance at finding his forever home. All in all, Parsley just wants to be loved!

Parsley didn't get the proper socialization he needed as a puppy, therefore he needs some work with other animals. Currently, he would do best in a home where is the only pet. He is a heavy sleeper, who loves to make "dens" with his blankets. He knows lots of commands, is potty trained, fixed and up to date on vaccines!

Are you the perfect forever home for Parsley?

Gender: Male

Spayed/neutered: Yes

Weight: 50 lbs

Vaccines: Rabies, Distemper, Bordetella

Heartworm results: Negative

Lyme results: Negative

Allergies: None

Special needs: Needs slow introductions

OK with kids: No

OK with cats: No

OK with dogs: No

Likes & dislikes: Loves ropes and stuffed animals

Adoption fee: $150

To Apply:

1) Print adoption application here:

https://staffordspca.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Stafford_SPCA_Adoption_Application_Adoption-Process-04182018.pdf

2) Email to adopt@staffordspca.org OR Fax to 866-522-8042.

Please see our website for details on our adoption process, and feel free to email with any questions about the process or about the pet you're interested in.

Home visits required and dog adoptions often do require structural fencing. (We make decisions regarding the fencing requirement on a dog-by-dog basis, according to the dog's exercise needs and energy level.)
Stafford SPCA does not condone the exclusive use of invisible fencing.
We reserve the right to deny placement of puppies and kittens into homes with children under 5 years old.

If you can't adopt, please sponsor me!

You can also volunteer; Get more information at www.staffordspca.org

animal.description:
ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS
Fenced yard
Canine sibling


My name is Jack. I am a 6 year old Lab/ Heeler mix and I am in the market for a new home. When my human was forced to move my brother and I weren't able to go. This nice rescue was able to find a foster home for me to stay while I look for a new family. I am about 75lbs which for my body type is way too much...lol. I guess we were fed well. My foster mom has me on an eating plan and I have actually lost some weight since coming to her but I need to lose a bit more to continue to be healthy. 
I am good with older kids and I need another dog in my new home. One that is pretty laid back and not all up in my face like some can be. A fenced yard is a must for exercise and pottying reasons. I walk well on a leash and actually love going for walks but have always had a yard to do my business. Someone who is home a lot would be great also. I am completely housebroken and well past the chewing stage of life. I also think I am a lap dog. I am a pretty quiet boy but I will bark if something out of the norm happens like doorbell or someone outside passing by. Did I also mention that I LOVE car rides? I will go anywhere you want to go if it means going in the car. 

If you would like to meet jack, send us an email to theloveofk9s@yahoo.com and we will get back with you as quick as we can

Adoption donation pays for all vetting...my neuter, a heart worm test, all vaccinations, deworming, flea prevention, a microchip and a wellness exam

To inquire about this dog,
- if you HAVE NOT previously submitted an application to our organization, please submit one at https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/AAP/Dog.
- if you HAVE previously submitted an application to our organization, email us at dogs@adoptapetfenton.com and let us know the name under which you submitted the application.

Do NOT call our center. We usually respond via email within 24-48 hours; please check your spam folder if you don't hear from us.

Often there is very little known about our dogs' and puppies' history or even current habits. We are best guessing on breed blends. We can't guarantee there is or isn't a specific breed in their breed blend.

You can always expect to do training, regardless of whether you adopt a dog or a puppy, including crate training, house training, and basic manners. Expect a 10+ year financial, physical, and emotional commitment to this canine. We provide a variety of materials and resources to assist you with this. All dogs and especially puppies are a lot of work and a long financial commitment. Please research what it means to have a dog and make sure a dog is still going to be an important part of your life in 10-15 years. All dogs and puppies need a lot of patience and guidance.

Most dogs who are in shelters will need an adjustment period after adoption. No matter how nice our shelter is and how much attention they get from our volunteers, it is not a home and they will need time to acclimate and get rid of some nervous energy.

Hi, my name is Poppa! I'm estimated to be a Pit mix born around 11/26/2016.  I weight around 66 pounds.  I am an energetic and friendly dog.  I'll need plenty of exercise in my new home.  I also am overly eager about my food so I need to be fed in an area where I can be by myself.  I also use a special food bowl that causes me to eat slowly as I tend to just gobble it all in one big mouthful. I love to play and also love to cuddle so I have a lot of good in me too!  Obedience classes for adult dogs and puppies can be incredibly helpful for both animals and humans. It helps you understand what makes me tick and will give me a better idea of what you want me to do. It’s a win/win and it will also strengthen the bond between us! Apply for me today!

My adoption fee is $60.00. Adoption applications can be filled out at CCHS or online through our website, www.cchs-petshelter.org. Applications are not first come, first served. All applications will be reviewed by the adoption committee and the home chosen will be the one considered to be the best match. All dogs and puppies have been vaccinated for Distemper and Bordetella, dewormed and microchipped. If old enough, they will be vaccinated for Rabies and blood tested for Heartworm, Lymes, Anaplasmosis and Erlichiosis. Dogs and puppies will be spayed or neutered before adoption.

CCHS is proud to be a No-Kill Humane Society. As a private, non-profit charity, our work depends on donations and volunteers to keep going. We are committed to helping the animals that enter our doors and finding each the best possible forever home. CCHS has been inspected and licensed by the Department of Animal Health - DATCP. Our license is #268235-DS

Midnight needs a fenced in yard because he loves exploring his environment. He should not go to a home with children, or a home where children may visit.

animal.description:
Gorgeous Glory is a very sweet 7 year old who is residing in a foster home and available for adoption. Below is information from her foster mom about how she is in a home:

She is house trained, rarely barks or wines, does not obsessively lick, does not get on the furniture, does not counter surf for food, sticks to her toys and does not chew furniture or other things. She is a good girl!

Her hair is short and she barely sheds. 

She loves walks and sits very still when you put on the leash. She walks nicely while on a leash.

She travels well in the car although is a little worried about getting in. 
She is friendly with people.

She does not get along with other dogs so needs to be an only dog in her new home.

Glory is food motivated, which has made training easier. She is smart and observant. She knows sit, stay, shake, lay down, come. 

She hates the crate, but is being fed in there with the door open to try to normalize it.

She is not a cuddly dog, but as she has gotten more comfortable, she is coming over for petting. She usually wants to be in the room where we are even if keeping a little distance. 

She is high energy and is very playful with balls, stuffed animals, etc.

She can be food and toy possessive. We are working on that, but taking it slowly. 

She needs a family with no children under 12. This girl was surrendered by her owner because she was afraid of the children. She did not harm or threaten them since she is such a sweet girl, she is just timid and small children make her uncomfortable.


Interested in adopting? Go on our website, triadspca.org and submit an application or call us at 336-375-3222.

animal.description:
HEY! I’m Snoopy!! Yes, I know I’m cute. I am a bit of a wild man and I am looking for an active family to keep up with me! I was dumped out in the country and the cool folks at ARF looked for my family but I guess they didn’t want me back. I am a sweet, young Terrier mix; approximately 2-3 years old and I weigh 23 lbs. I can climb a 6-ft. chainlink fence so I will need a privacy fence or suitable alternative to keep me in and safe, though it's likely I won't WANT to go anywhere once I find my forever family. 

I am a very sweet guy and I love people! I have LOADS of energy and will need plenty of stimulation; walks, car rides and tons of play time! Because I have so much energy, I probably wouldn’t be suited for an apartment; I’ll need access to a backyard to go out to play when I need to get some of that energy out. All I really want is a family to love and call my own. 

The fee to adopt Snoopy is $200.00; this includes spay/neuter, deworming, vaccinations and a microchip. If you are interested in adopting Snoopy, please visit our website. www.arfhouse.org and fill out an adoption application. 

**Please Note: Snoopy is currently located at our facility in Sherman, Texas. Adoptions are by-appointment only; if you would like to meet Snoopy, please fill out an application on our website. Once we have your application, our Adoption Coordinator will follow up with you ASAP with any questions she may have, or to set up a meet-and-greet.

animal.description:
Just simply Jeb....I am a 2 yr old neutered male Shep mix and I weigh 46 lbs. So let's be completely transparent....I. Am. A. Lap. Dog. Feel so much better now that I told you....I love to lick, rub and waller all over my hooman....so there's that too. I'm full of energy so I need someone who can keep up the pace. I love toys and food....which brings me to the next thing I need to be honest about....I'm not fond of my food being touched when I eat...that being said it would be best for me to eat in a secured area so others aren't tempted to touch my food. I do love other dogs....and I'm ready to play at first sight! Come see me soon....I'm available now! Adopting a dog from the Conway Animal Welfare Unit is a fairly easy process. The first step to adopting an animal is submitting an application. The application allows us to individually consider applicants and helps us to properly match our pets with new owners. We want to make sure that our pets are going to homes that are ready to provide for these pets long-term. Adoptions are $50 and this includes vaccinations, heartworm test, spay/neuter and microchip. As with any shelter animal, health is not guaranteed but we do our best to screen out those animals that are showing obvious signs of illness or disclose that information prior to adoption. All dogs are heartworm tested upon adoption. 

If you are interested in adopting a dog and you reside OUTSIDE the city limits of Conway and the dog is less than 12 wks old, the cost is $75 which includes a spay/neuter and micropchip. The spay and neuter can only be performed at Vilonia Vet Clinic or Companion Animal Spay/Neuter Clinic. If the animal is less that 12 wks and you live inside the city limits the adoption fee is $25 dollars and you receive a voucher for $120 to use at select clinics for spay/neuter. The other option is that you provide us with proof of a pre-paid spay or neuter at YOUR vet of choice.

animal.description:
Please meet bonded buddies Timon & Pumba!  Timon is a white & tan chihuahua with green eyes and weighs 7 pounds and Pumba is a toy cairn terrier weighing 15 pounds (he is currently on a diet) They are both 5 years old. These  sweet boys were found running down a dirt road out in the country together. They play together,  they sleep together and are looking for their forever home together.  Pumba is just the sweetest while Timon who is also sweet can be a little more bossy (typical chi).  Pumba loves to eat, loves treats and prefers to be wherever his human is... same with Timon except he has to be in your lap or as close as he can possibly get.  They get along well with other dogs and don't mind cats!  
These boys will need a special home together because Timon has a heart murmur that he takes medication for twice a day & Pumba has a seizure disorder that he also takes medication for twice a day.  They are both doing extremely well and are now ready for their forever family.  
ALL adoptions require a completed application, vet check, home check and final contract.  The application to adopt can be found at www.camorescue.com.

Adoption fees are variable. Up to date vaccines, microchip, spay/neuter are included in the fee.

Once your application has been approved, we will put you in touch with the foster to set up a  meet and greet. We are a foster based RESCUE, not a shelter. All of our dogs are in individual foster homes. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We select the best applicant for each dog, based on the dog's needs. 
For the safety of our small breed dogs and based on our past experiences, we will not place our dogs in homes with large breed dogs.    

CAMO rescue is a 501c3 whose primary focus is rescuing small dogs from the euthanasia list from high kill TX shelters.   
EIN # is 46-5486022
We rescue 800+ animals a year.

Timon is a white & tan chihuahua with green eyes and weighs 7 pounds and Pumba is a toy cairn terrier weighing 15 pounds (he is currently on a diet) They are both 5 years old. These  sweet boys were found running down a dirt road out in the country together. They play together,  they sleep together and are looking for their forever home together.  Pumba is just the sweetest while Timon who is also sweet can be a little more bossy (typical chi).  Pumba loves to eat, loves treats and prefers to be wherever his human is... same with Timon except he has to be in your lap or as close as he can possibly get.  They get along well with other dogs and don't mind cats!  
These boys will need a special home together because Timon has a heart murmur that he takes medication for twice a day & Pumba has a seizure disorder that he also takes medication for twice a day.  They are both doing extremely well and are now ready for their forever family.

All of our dogs are in individual foster homes. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We select the best applicant for each dog, based on the dog's needs. 
For the safety of our small breed dogs and based on our past experiences, we will not place our dogs in homes with large breed dogs.    

CAMO rescue is a 501c3 whose primary focus is rescuing small dogs from the euthanasia list from high kill TX shelters.

We rescue 800+ animals a year.

animal.description:
Diego’s eyes beg you to consider loving him, and if you do, he will love you back tenfold.  He is a 5-year-old Shepherd (mix) that weighs 60 pounds. He responds to the words:  SIT, WAIT, LEAVE-IT, GET IT, BRING IT, DROP IT, OFF, TAKE IT, and TOUCH IT.  He loves pleasing the people he knows and whoever is fortunate enough to adopt him will quickly learn that Diego is waiting to live and die for you.

One of his greatest joys is playing ball with someone he loves.  He can catch a ball for an hour without getting bored, and afterwards he will cool off in any body of water he finds. He loves spending time outside exploring in our big fenced yards. He thinks going for car a ride anytime to anywhere is a great thing to do. But at the end of the day, he really enjoys just relaxing on a soft spot in an air conditioned or comfortable room.  He is clean in his environment and has proven to be house trained with good manners, in a home he recently stayed in for a couple of weeks. He also enjoyed their fenced back yard and did not try to dig or climb out.  Unfortunately, the people were not equipped to adopt him.


Diego has spent time at the facility of one of our trainers (Denise), playing in her big yards with other dogs.  We learned, if there is another dog in Diego’s family, he would do best with a dog his size that does not try to push him around.  Diego is very happy to have canine companionship but it has to be the RIGHT dog.  He knows how to take behavior cues from other dogs. That said, Diego can be too much for some dogs, so he would not be a good candidate to take to dog parks. Planned play dates with compatible dogs would be best.
 

Diego spent one wet day at an adoption event at Devils Backbone Basecamp. Dogs and people were all closely collected in the areas that had cover from the rain, and Diego was very well behaved.  He loved the attention from people, and though he wanted very much to play with the other dogs and would yip and want to go up to sniff and say hi. He was still VERY good at listening to his handlers when told to leave it and settle down.  He sat nicely to greet people and wagged his tail with happiness .  He regularly enjoyed jogging around the perimeter of the site with his human buddy to catch a tennis ball and play in puddles.  He didn’t pull or try to get away as he sniffed, trotted about, and caught his ball.  He had quite the fan club among venue guests but no compatible households for him.

Diego is a perfect match for ACTIVE adopters who can give him regular exercise, mental stimulation, and put in a little time to establish boundaries and reinforce his manners.  He will love to join his owners on hikes or other outdoor activities. Diego has a great foundation of obedience and manners that should transition well into a home.  He needs an owner who will enable him to be his best self by commitment to follow through with his training.  He loves balls, toys water and people.  He’s just a great all-around guy.

If you have another dog and are interested in meeting Diego, contact Denise at info@campmerricks.com.  She can set up a meeting away from the shelter.  Diego is selective about the dogs he likes.  He is not good with cats and is too much dog for children under 12.  If you have the right home for Diego, he will keep you smiling, help you keep your body toned, make you feel safe, will listen to all your complaints, will try and do anything you ask, will lie at your feet, will keep you company on car drives, an most of all will love you more than you can fantasize.

Diego is NOT located at the Middleburg Humane Foundation—he is in a Central Virginia shelter 2½ hours from there.  If you are interested in Diego please go to our website www.nelsonspca.org and fill out an on-line application and someone from our shelter will get back to you quickly
 
You may also contact Flower at 434-361-0190 or ek.gk@verizon.net to chat about Diego too.

animal.description:
Bindi is smart, she knows sit, stay (not to obedience training levels, but well enough to not bolt out the door as you go out), no, drop it, and leave it. She's pretty good at fetching, but not so much at letting go, so it works best if you have two of what you're throwing. She will then drop the one she has at your feet (or close) and you can throw the other one.

She knows the names of two of the toy types we will send with her. The Kongs are wubbles, and the balls with handles are quaffles.

She loves peanut butter, pumpkins (we've given her the tiny ones), bananas, carrots, apples, and oranges. Along with standard dog treats, a few pieces of a different flavor of kibble also work as a treat.

However, she is afraid of basically everything.

When playing if we tell her to go easy she will pick up a toy so it becomes tug of war instead of wrestling, and they've both been learning the command time out. While she and our other dog get along great most of the time, and she shows interest in other dogs, she'd likely do best in an only dog household with no small children. Her occasional overactions are the issue because she takes them out on the other dog. She has never deliberately bitten any person, but if one gets between it's like she isn't even aware they are there once a fight starts and she bites whatever is in front of her.

She does have a bad knee, but does well with glucosamine.

She is spayed, her shots are all, current, and she has been on Heart Guard basically her whole life.

animal.description:
Tootsie Roll is a 6 year old female Wirehaired Terrier Mix rescued as an owner surrender. They could not give her the care she deserves. She was living in a cold building and often got out on a busy street. 

If you think you would be interested, please complete our no obligation application and we can start the process at www.luv4k9s.org. Select Available Dogs then scroll down to application, complete and submit. 

A physical secure fence attached to the residence is a requirement to adopt a dog from our rescue. Invisible fence doesn't meet this requirement. No exceptions.

Our adoption area is primarily OHIO. We will consider KENTUCKY, AND INDIANA AND CERTAIN AREAS OF MICHIGAN, WEST VIRGINIA, AND PENNSYLVANIA if it’s the best fit for the dog.

WE DO NOT SHIP NOR ARRANGE TRANSPORTS.

THE APPLICATION MUST BE COMPLETED AND SUBMITTED BEFORE WE CAN START THE PROCESS. 

IT CAN TAKE AT LEAST 2 WEEKS TO PROCESS AN APPLICATION SOMETIMES LONGER DEPENDING ON VOLUNTEER AVAILABILITY AND NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS RECEIVED SO PLEASE BE PATIENT. 

NOTE TO EMAILERS FROM PETFINDER: WE DO NOT RESPOND TO EMAIL INQUIRIES WITHOUT AN APPLICATION. WE REGRET WE CANNOT RESPOND TO EVERY EMAIL, BUT UNLESS YOU FILL OUT AN APPLICATION, WE DO NOT KNOW YOU EXIST. 

All known information about an individual dog is provided in its listing. We do our best to provide accurate information, but adopters must understand that each home is different, and the dog may behave differently in a new home. Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. 
Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for:
1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (ex. a 4 month old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break) 
2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old, to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise.
3.) Socialization: The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home.
4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded tenfold, for years to come.
Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy. Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time consuming and can be expensive. All Dogs Require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well-trained, well socialized dog is more than worth the effort put in to get them there. 

Our adoption fee includes spay/neuter, routine shots, rabies, worming, microchipped, heartworm testing and they are on monthly preventative. Visit our website www.luv4k9s.org for more information and to complete an application.

animal.description:
**Please read the whole post before asking to adopt me **

Hi world, I am Joey. I am a special needs boy, who is looking for my forever home I am around 5 months old, my mom says I am a mutt of some sort. They did purchase a DNA test that will tell everyone just what I am! How neat is that?! I am around 15 pounds, and I dont think I will get much bigger, I am a petite guy. My metabolism is out of this world with all of my activity.

So here is the deal, I know I am cute.. I know you want to kiss and love me but I am just not a normal puppy. I have a neurological condition that causes me to consistently spin. That means I will never be able to just walk into a pet store, or stay out of a kennel when you leave, or sleep in bed with you unless its very low to the ground. Safety is important with my condition. My mom lets me go outside by myself and play with all my friends, they are so much fun. They are so gentle with me and sometimes, I run in a straight line, especially to get back inside!

I had an MRI done, and costed my rescue lots of money..hehe.. well that showed a change in my brain tissue on the right side of the brain. There is an area consistent with bleeding and loss of brain tissue. This is from a severe trauma, I wish I could tell you what happened to me. My doctors and specialist think that my condition will remain the same, with no improvement or declining. I do have loss of vision in both eyes, but mainly the left.

Some of my absolute favorite things to do:
- Play outside with my friends
- Poop on moms floor
- Play with all of these fun toys
- Couch snuggles
- Car rides & meeting strangers

I am working on potty training, but honestly I may never be able to be fully potty trained. I do wear a wrap when playing inside because I pee & then spin in a circle creating a sprinkler.

I require a home with patience, and unconditional love. If you think that you can take care of me forever, please email my foster momma > dakota@adoptionfirstky.com

 Cincinnati or tri state area

**Please see the videos in the comments**

animal.description: Meet Cameron! He is a 1 year old Doberman mix who weighs about 40 lbs. He came into a Tennessee shelter with a badly injured back leg which had to be amputated.  Never fear, because he gets around just as well as a 4 legged dog! Cameron is an active boy who must go to a home with another dog who loves to play as much as he does. He tends to get mouthy with kids when he gets excited,  so a home with no kids is preferred. He is house and crate trained and gets along well with dogs of all sizes. We are not sure how he is with cats. A physically fenced yard is required with his adoption. True to his breed, he is extremely intelligent and loyal. He is neutered,  up to date on shots and microchipped.  His adoption fee is $250.00. If you have questions not covered in this bio,  please email projecthoperescue@gmail.com. To apply to adopt,  visit our website at www.projecthoperescue.org.

animal.description:
PLEASE VISIT OUR WEBSITE AT WWW.PITRESCUE.ORG FOR INFORMATION ON OUR ORGANIZATION, ADOPTION POLICIES AND PROCESS, EDUCATIONAL INFORMATION, AND A FULL LIST OF OUR ADOPTABLE DOGS ALONG WITH PHOTOS AND FULL BIOS!!!
More pictures and info on this particular dog visit: https://www.pitrescue.org/brigid

Apply online: http://fs22.formsite.com/siouxempire/form1/index.html?1316620486706

*Adoption application must be filled out with home visit and references (personal and vet) required prior to any adoption. Filling out an application does not obligate you to adopt, but merely begins the process. SEPR DOES adopt out of state!

Adoption fees: All SEPR adoptions are $300 for adults and $400 for puppies 1 year and under.  This includes: adoption fee (spay/neuter, utd vaccinations, micro-chipping), microchip registration, Gentle Leader, and two tie downs for use in your home. 

SEPR requires all adopted dogs attend a training class with their adoptive family within 90 days of their adoption. If an adoptive family completes this training class, they will be refunded $100 of their adoption fee with proof of licensed certificate. SEPR even offers an obedience class called Train-A-Bull to alumni over 1 year of age on a seasonal basis.  These classes are currently free!

*All other pets in the residence must be spayed or neutered and all pets up to date on vaccinations.

*SEPR requires all applicants must be 21 years of age.

*SEPR dogs are adopted to be inside the home, “part of the family” dogs only.

*Families with children 5 years of age and under wanting to adopt puppies will be reviewed on a case by case basis. Raising a puppy properly takes a lot of time, and we understand that in families with small children, time can be a limited commodity.

animal.description: Roan is such a rambunctious boy! Whether he's happily wrestling with his doggie foster brother or playing chase, he just loves having fun. He'll even drop a bone in front of his human friends so they'll toss it for him. Then this energetic, playful boy is just as happy to chill and cuddle with them on the couch. He's a loyal boy who follows his people everywhere. He walks well on his leash, interested in other dogs he sees. And he answers to 'sit.' At home, he may be reluctant to go in his crate, but once there he's content to sleep quietly. And when he's out, this silly boy is happy to chew on his Nylabone. Roan would love a home with someone who can take him for runs and/or who has active older kids to play with. Come meet this friendly boy. He'll even love to do Netflix binges with you! Also, follow his antics on Instagram @adoptroan.

animal.description: 14 is the new 7! Bridle does not let her age or her health issues keep her down! This little lady does indeed love to snooze and chill for a good portion of the day but she also LOVES to go on walkies and have play time in the yard. When she she is excited to see her favorite human friends or when it is time for breakfast she jumps around like a puppy, barely able to contain her excitement. She prefers to be with people when possible so would do best with somebody who has a more flexible schedule or is home most of the time. She does well with other small doggies that won't jump on her and get too rowdy with her. She is teeny tiny y'all! She would probably do well with older kids that won't bother her when she is resting or be too rough with her. You should know that sweet Bridle does have diabetes. Due to her condition she needs a strict diet of special food and requires 2 insulin shots each day. It may take 2 people to give her the shot. Do you have room for this wonderful lady in your home? Please inquire on the website

Kaiser, excellent young dog, a fabulous mix of maybe, Rottweiler, Shepherd mix,   , approx 2 years old, is a super young dog!
He is a mixed breed of LOVE, fun, sweet, playful,  tries hard to please and is so  handsome and UNUSUAL!! He is so sweet and loving, playful and great in a home and out for walks, hiking, shopping, anything you want to do! We have no idea what his combination of mixed breed is  but hes fabulous! 
He is kind enough to help our friend Chunky Monkey find confidence and get over her sadness when she came to LBWF.
He is perfect for the active family or person wanting to enjoy activities.
LBWF raced to his rescue when we hear about what a great dog he is. The family that had him fell on hard times, as so many this year. he passed his obedience classes at Petco, loved all dogs, kids, super playful and fun, loved hiking and activities and was a wonderful family member, but they could no longer afford to keep him.
 He has a magnificent black coat with multi color speckling,  
He loves to play, snuggle, watch TV, go for car rides, beach, restaurants.   
Loves to play and is so loving! He wants a home of his own again so bad!!!
 Southern Ca adoptions only due to home checks.
He is ready to go to his forever loving home!
Up to date on shots, neutered and micro chipped!
Please fill out an application at www.LindaBlairWorldheart.org and tell us why you are the right home for this fun loving boy!
To see all of our dogs available for adoption please visit www.LindaBlairWorldheart.org  under the Adopt Today tab. To view more pictures of the dogs in action please visit our Facebook page www.Facebook.com/LindaBlairWorldheartFoundation

animal.description:
Fido is in need of a forever home because her owner recently passed away. Fido is a rough coated Jack Russell terrier and about 14 years old and weighs 17 pounds. She is smart, alert, attentive, loving, spry.   She likes to stay close to her human and thoroughly enjoys walks, car rides, sitting on the sofa curled up. She will act like a puppy and will do tricks for treats and loves being spoiled with love and treats. 

As most Jack Russell terriers, she likes to be top dog and therefore will need a home with no other pets or small children. She shouldn’t be brought to a dog park or out where other dogs may run up and startle her.  She prefers her human companion over other dogs.  She is looking to be in a home where she would get loving attention and not be left for long periods of time.  She will need a yard for safe daytime access to go to the bathroom or hang out and get some sun and mostly just hang out with her human. animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.*Update 1/8/2021*
Ida best checking in. This year has been really good to me. I found a foster home that is ready to foster me until I find my FUREVER family. I am really loving my new foster family. I get so much attention being the only one. I just have so much love to share. Are you willing to open up your home for endless kisses and snuggles?

*Update 12/12/20*
I am checking with my fan group. I have recently been told that I can not live with cats or little dogs as I think they are toys, so I need a home with NO CATS or SMALL DOGS. I do well with polite big dogs and I love to alternate between gentle play, naps, and treats. I also love little humans.

With all the medical appointments I have had recently to figure out what is up with my tumor, we still don't have all the answers. I have a little bit of a hiccup with my non-tumor back leg so the doctors think that a full leg amputation would not be a good idea as it will put too much stress on it. And the tumor itself can not be removed safely. Thankfully I am unbothered by the tumor and barely notice it, nor does it hinder my daily life!

I will need a home with the understanding that this tumor might be a bit tricky if it keeps growing and what to expect if and when something happens to it!

*New to rescue*
My name is Ida Best and I am the best. I was found wandering the streets of Dallas TWICE in the last year and this last time, my family didn't reclaim me. I have a large mass on my back leg and some fur loss but I still am in happy and sweet spirits. I love to be covered by a blankie and I pout when I have my sweaters in the wash.

Stay tuned as we get some idea of what is medical going on with sweet Ida Best.

animal.description:
Tofu is a big 3 year old male Golden Retriever mix who recently arrived in the US from Turkey. He’s been great with settling in and getting acclimated in his new foster home. Tofu is potty trained, knows how to ‘sit’ and loves to be a giant big lap dog when he gets tired and jumps on the couch with you. Though he is tall enough to reach the counters, he’s been very respectful of not grabbing food. He will bark a bit when new person comes into the house, but then wags his tail and wants all the loving once he realizes they’re his new best friend…and he seems to love everyone he meets. He is a very high energy dog and loves to be outside – he would run around in a big, secure backyard or go on walks all day long if he could! He’s great on leash with people and other dogs, but thinks squirrels are fun to chase. Everyone that’s met him so far, falls in love. We’re still learning more about Tofu and what he’s looking for in a forever home, so check back for more updates!

Note: Tofu would fit best in a home with children above the age of 7.

If you are interested in adopting from us, please complete an adoption application at our website (www.fetchinretrieversrescue.org). Once your application is received, it will be reviewed and you may be contacted to arrange a home visit. In keeping with our adoption process, there are no meet and greets with a dog until all steps in the application process have been completed and a potential match has been made. We adhere to this policy because we strive to ensure adoption success between dogs and their new family.
