animal.description:
If this listing is still posted, we are still accepting applications for him/her. We do not do out-of-state adoptions on highly adoptable dogs; we would only consider out-of-state adoptions for dogs that prove hard-to-place locally. We cannot hold dogs, please submit your application when you are ready to adopt. PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING PARAGRAPHS FOR INFORMATION ON THIS DOG, AS WELL AS INFORMATION ON OUR PROCESS.

Robert is around 4-6 years old and weighs 60 pounds. He is EXTREMELY sweet with people. He has not yet been tested with dogs, but has not shown any signs of aggression if a dog passes by the fence. Rescued as a stray, Robert is grateful to have a roof over his head and be an indoor pet. He is crate-trained, clean and well-behaved. He obeys well and knows "sit" and "high-five." He is a pretty mellow and low-key guy, but eager to please his humans. He loves hugs and cuddles. He is quite loyal and especially loving. Robert is a truly wonderful dog with an equally lovely temperament to match! His adoption fee is $295 which covers the cost of his neuter, all core vaccines (Rabies and Distemper/Parvo), microchip and microchip registration. If you’d like to be considered for adoption, the first step is completing an application which is available on our website, poochmatch.com, under the adoption tab. Please read the below paragraphs for more information on our process.

UPDATE: ADOPTION EVENTS CANCELLED DUE TO PANDEMIC AND SOCIAL DISTANCING. If you are interested in meeting any Poochmatch dog at our weekly adoption event on Saturdays at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda, CA (5521 Mirage St.) between 1-5 PM, please fill out an application from our website, poochmatch.com, and submit it no later than 11 AM on Fridays. Upon receipt AND approval, the dog you are interested in meeting will be made available to meet on a Saturday. Due to the high volume of dogs and puppies in our foster homes, it is impossible to bring them all every Saturday. The only way to ensure that the dog that you are interested in will be at the adoption event is to FILL OUT AN APPLICATION AND BE APPROVED. Otherwise, we cannot guarantee that the dog you are interested in will be at our adoption event. If you cannot make the time frame of our events, appointments can be made at another time and location solely at the discretion of the foster parent. Please understand that private appointments will be coordinated to meet the convenience of the foster parent/transporter.

All adoption fees cover the mandatory and non-negotiable spay/neuter, rabies, microchip, microchip registration, full sets of core vaccinations (rabies and 1 set of distemper/parvo for adults, 4 for puppies) and deworming. Adoption fees vary based on age, breed, size and the costs incurred on the dog's behalf by us i.e. medical, behavioral training, etc. and they range from $225-$495.


COVID-19 PROCEDURE:
In an effort to create a safe environment for our potential adopters and our staff, we have changed our protocols and procedures during these difficult times. Starting immediately, our procedures will change from what’s written on our website and other social media platforms. Our weekly adoption event at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda is temporarily cancelled due to COVID-19 and social distancing. The only way to meet one of the dogs/puppies we have available for adoption is through completion of our adoption application through our website, poochmatch.com, before 11 AM on Fridays. On Fridays when we review the applications, we will pick the best fit for each dog or puppy applied for and coordinate mutually agreeable appointment times for the applicants who are approved that week. Private appointments are currently only scheduled on Wednesday, Thursday or Saturday of each week. Masks or bandanas are mandatory; faces must be properly covered.

With the overwhelming desire of the public to adopt at this time, we have received as many as 30 applications for one dog in just one week. Working with a staff of volunteers, we are only able to reach out on Fridays to the people we have approved to adopt. If you have not heard from us by Friday, we have selected a different applicant. If you have multiple dogs/puppies that you are interested in, please indicate each dog/puppy of interest on the application at that time so we don’t rule you out for another dog/puppy available for adoption.

Please understand, we have an influx of texts, phone calls and emails that makes it impossible to get to each and every one of you. Not just for adoption interest, but also from veterinarians, people who must relinquish dogs, people who have found a stray dog in need of pick up, etc. We are currently not in need of fosters. Due to the fact that there is such a high demand, we are sticking with strict protocol to not adopt out of Southern California. We apologize for this inconvenience and difficulty to be able to get in touch with us while there is an overwhelming desire and demand to adopt at this time. We appreciate your understanding and patience as we navigate through these difficult times with every intention to keep the public and our staff safe.

animal.description:
Hey, I’m Connie! I try not to brag, but the fact is I am a Gorgeous American Bulldog mix with white hair, blue eyes, and a pink spotted nose. 
I am spayed, up to date on vaccinations, and Heartworm positive - but I'm going through slow kill treatment currently! 
I was born about a year or two ago and was struggling in a rural Louisiana shelter when Take Paws rescued me. Because it’s been a rough road getting here, I take my time to warm up to people, especially men. I’ve got to make sure I’m safe! 
But once I know I am safe, boy oh boy, will I make your heart melt as I show you the true cuddly 50 lb lap dog that I am! 
My white coat is no coincidence, because I strongly believe in my role as your self-appointed guardian angel. As your guardian angel, I always want to protect you, and I don’t take the job lightly. This can lead to me showing some serious guarding and defensive behaviors towards other people and dogs. I am selective about who I deem worthy of being near me, because I know what a special girl I am!
 I love long walks and lots of exercise, and I love love love playing and snuggling with my foster siblings. However they’ve got to know I’m the Alpha lady of the household, the big boss. I follow my foster mom around everywhere; I love the company and attention!!! 
I’m an amazing girl to have on your team, but I need someone who will be patient and willing to work with me longterm. Please let me know if that’s you!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2020 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

animal.description:
Animal Profile: Marley is an adorable chihuahua/terrier mix who was rescued from southern CA, along with 4 other buddies. He is estimated to be around 1-2 years old, and weighs around 10lbs.

Foster Update: Marley is a very special boy, looking for a special forever home to call his own! Marley was rescued with 4 of his buddies as they were found running the streets of rural CA. Marley was very timid when he first arrived, and it became apparent he hadn't had much interaction with humans or being in a home setting. After lots of decompression, training, and learning to be a dog, Marley has now really come out of his shell. He loves his dog friends, and he will need a canine companion in his forever home. He loves to romp around, play chase, and most of all - curl up on a couch together. He really gains a lot of his confidence with a dog buddy, and it's been so great to see his tail wagging when he has a buddy to play with. He absolutely loves stuffed animals/toys, and is quite motivated by high value treats. Marley also enjoys chew bones, plush blankets, and burrowing.

Marley has done great with his humans, once he has had some time to build trust. He is still quite timid with new people, but that's slowly improving. He can be timid/skittish at first, and needs a human who will not only take things slow but also play the confident role to help him come out of his shell. Marley was able to visit with a few members of our team for a few days each, and it took him a day or two to decompress but then started asking for pets and lap time. He really needs a human who can advocate for him, and help give him a confidence push so that he doesn't fall back into his fearful ways. He will freeze on leash when in new situations, and often try and pull away - it's important for his human to have calm confidence to show him "hey, we got this!" and help him move forward, rather than reinforce his fearfulness. He really responds well to guidance and direction and quickly learns, "hey, that wasn't so bad after all!".

Once Marley settles in, he enjoys walks and beach time but doesn't do well with busy city areas/high traffic areas. We are looking for a forever home for Marley with a canine companion, as he absolutely loves having a dog to play with and there hasn't been a dog he's met yet that he didn't love. Marley will also require a home with a fully fenced yard. While he has improved greatly on leash, Marley can get overwhelmed with new/loud noises and would enjoy a space where he can safely run and play. While he enjoys casual strolls, a safe yard to play in is really more his jam. Because Marley is more timid, we are requiring an adult-only home, with preference to past experience with timid dogs.

It's been an absolute joy to see Marley's true personality start to shine, and for him to show of his goofy and playful personality. Marley is going to make an amazing addition to a lucky person(s) who is patient and ready to help Marley continue to grow and flourish.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued from euthanasia at a high-kill shelter in California and will be available for adoption in Seattle, once evaluated in a loving foster home in the greater Seattle area.

animal.description:
Missy's date of birth was 11/2018. She is a deaf purebred Dogo Argentino. She comes from show lines and was born deaf. She was sent to us by her breeder to give her the best chance of finding a committed forever family. Missy has UKC papers.
She's very smart, and she's a BIG girl! She's also extremely affectionate, loves other dogs, and is a lot of fun to play with. She is full of personality and will put a smile on your face every day.

Missy is able to live with other dogs, but may be overwhelming for me smaller or older dogs. She would do best as the only dog in the home due to her size and breed traits.
Dogo Argentinos were bred to be powerful and persistent hunters of large game. They need to be included with the family, trained, and socialized. They will also require quite a bit of exercise, activity and mental stimulation. Please do your homework on the breed, as Dogos are not recommended for first time dog owners. They can be formidable adult dogs who require their people to have advanced dog handling skills, or be willing to learn. Outdoor only homes will not be considered.
We are seeking guardians that will provide Missy with what she needs on a daily basis. Follow-up with training will be required, and will be part of the adoption contract. We do include training with local adoptions.
To meet Missy, please complete our online application for adoption: www.deafdogrescueofamerica.org/adoption-application.html

Please note that we are unable to respond to inquiries, emails or phone calls. Our adoption process starts with completion/submission of an application for adoption. All applications are reviewed as quickly as we can, and our adoption process is not first come, first served. We select our adoptive homes according to what our dogs/puppies require. If you are selected as an appropriate match, you will be contacted to set an appointment to visit the Ranch and meet Missy.

animal.description:
We are currently accepting applications to adopt Vegas. If you are interested in meeting and adopting her, please submit an adoption application by visiting our website (www.HarborOfHopeDogRescue.org). Due to COVID19 safety measures, meetings are currently only being scheduled with approved adopters.

Vegas is a 2yo Lab/Staffy mix, wieghing approx 56lbs and this mom made a big impression and said Welcome to Las Vegas in a new way for the rescue when she had her litter of 9 mid transport up from Amarillo, TX. Good with other dogs and indifferent about cats, Vegas is a big bundle of love!! She worked with United Paws Dog Training to master her basic skills like sit, walking well on a leash, and all of the other imporant things to build the best resume! She is potty trained and kennel trained but would LOVE to sleep with her favorite human at night! 

She is great with kids and pretty much anyone that wants to give her love. Especially if you will let her be a lap dog! Are you the lucky family to win big with this gal!

Per breed evaluation through Nebraska Humane Society, Vegas does not need to abide by Omaha Breed Specific Laws. 

All of our dogs are fully vetted before adoption, including vaccinations, spay/neuter, and a microchip.

The adoption process consists of an online application, a vet reference, two personal references, and a home visit. If approved to adopt, there is an adoption contract and an adoption amount. The adoption amount for Vegas is $325 and goes toward the vetting and care of all the dogs in our rescue.

All adoptions will take place in the Omaha NE area and must be done in person. We are willing to adopt to out-of-state applicants, contingent on our ability to complete a home visit, but you must be willing to come to the Omaha area to complete the adoption. We do not ship, transport or deliver our dogs.

If you would like to learn more about Harbor of Hope Dog Rescue, please visit our website (www.HarborOfHopeDogRescue.org) or our Facebook page. Thank you for your support!

animal.description: Everyone welcome Stella Rose!! Stella Rose is a 4-year-old female Staffordshire Terrier mix that was surrendered to our rescue by her family. Upon intake, we noticed that she was pretty sick. Our vet determined that she had pyometra and needed emergency surgery. Well, we are happy to report that she is all healed and now ready to find her forever home. Stella Rose is a happy go lucky girl who is as wide as she is tall. Although her weight is about 50 pounds, she looks like she is only about 30 pounds in person. She is what we would refer to as a baby Hippo. Stella Rose loves all people and kids. She walks great on a leash, knows her basic commands and is pottie trained. She is not really interested with other large dogs (and doesn't like them being in her business but is great in pack walks with them), so we are recommending a home with no other dogs. She does not do well with small dogs or small animals. She is very loving, happy and a very sweet dog. She would make a really nice family pet. Stella Rose has been spayed, is up to date on her vaccinations and is also microchipped. If interested in meeting or adopting Stella Rose, please go to www.LOLR.org and fill out an adoption application.

animal.description:
Come and meet the beautiful, resilient Coco Puff! Coco is a 48 lb mixed dog (her brother had an Embark dna test and his results are in her pictures) who was born in April 2020. 
She is full of energy and loves to chase her ball! She needs someone who is patient because she lived outside with her siblings until she was about 6 months old. She is learning basic commands such as sit, lay down and shake, but still jumps excitably when her foster parents come home and counter-surfs if given the chance. She walks pretty well on the leash but does pull when she sees another dog or squirrel. She has been attending group obedience classes and is perfecting her skills. 
Coco is kennel trained and almost completely housebroken. She gets along with her foster sibling but is reactive with excitement when meeting another dog. She has not been around children or cats. 
Coco is up to date on vaccines, heartworm negative, and spayed. 
At the end of the day, Coco loves to lounge on the couch and watch tv while chewing on her bone next to her foster family. She may be the perfect addition to your home!

 *Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2020 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300

animal.description:
I was adopted and returned because as much as I love humans, I simply can’t be with other dogs under ANY circumstances.  I need to live in a place with no other dogs nearby (i.e. fence neighbours).  I am happy getting my exercise in a fenced back yard.  I can NEVER go for walks or leave my secure yard in case I encounter another dog.  My lovely forever family forgot this and took me for a walk where I encountered another dog with disastrous results.  If I can’t find a family who understands this about me, GR might have to give up on me and they just don’t do that.  Yes, I am aggressive with other dogs and my trainer says this will never change, but I am a pussy cat with humans.  In fact, I have been described as a big, lazy (with some spurts of energy), calm, love bug and I’m okay with that description as it’s pretty accurate.  I’m really big…180 lbs (so in a way, you’d almost be adopting three Goldens ~ haha).  They call me JC after John Candy…get it?  I hardly ever bark.  I love being touched almost anywhere, but we can talk about that!  I love my food.  You can leave me alone if you have to go out without me.  I am gentle with my treats.  I can jump into the car no problem and I’m good in the car…although you’re not going to take me anywhere other than just for a drive or the odd trip to the vet (which also has to be arranged so that I don’t run into other dogs while there).  I’m not big on toys but I do love hanging out in the backyard sniffing and watching the world go by.  I know my commands and the doc says I’m healthy except my teeth need some work.  I’m ready to find my new forever family…and a calm, quiet family without young children would be best.  Anybody got space for me?  I do take up more room than your average Golden but that only means there’s more of me to love.  You know that baseball terms…three strikes and you’re out???  I’m getting close to that and I really need your help as I have also been a very expensive boy for Golden Rescue to board.  If you can live with my limitations, I promise to love you to the moon and back.

JC is currently being fostered in the Newmarket, ON area. If you would like more information about JC please call our hot-line toll free at 1-866-712-8444 or email adoption@goldenrescue.ca and one of our volunteers will be happy to return your call.

Molly is a 18 month old, female, lab mix. She is the sweetest pup you will ever meet. Giving birth to 7 beautiful puppies, she took on the nurturing role quickly with everyone she met. Molly is hopeful that she and her puppies will find their furever families to provide lots of love and affection. Molly is sweet natured, but still a young pup herself with loads of energy. About a week after being rescued by STARS, Molly gave birth to 7 little cuties who are now about 12 weeks old (18 weeks at adoption even in December). Molly and her puppies are all in search of their forever homes in time for the holidays! 
 
Click on www.starsrescue.org to complete an application to be pre-approved to adopt this pup. As you can imagine, we get a lot of interest in our rescues and kindly ask that you are patient with us while we review applications as it may take a few days.We will contact you regarding your application, during which you can ask more questions about this specific pup. Our adoption fee is $500. This includes spay/neuter, microchipping, deworming, and all age-appropriate vaccinations

animal.description:
Hi my name is Jade and how can you not notice how beautiful I am?  Foster mom says I have a gorgeous glossy coat with white markings that stand out.  Seriously, can you not see my cute white chin.

I’m a very sweet girl, with a good mix of chilling on the couch next to you and racing around outside.  I’m working on building my confidence when meeting new people and experiencing new things.  Foster mom and I are working with a trainer and so far, so good.  I love my walks around the lake and yummy treats make everything better! I love treats and they make my training so much fun!  Speaking of training, I know how to sit and lay down.  We’re also working on the “touch” command.  I’m crate trained as well and will sleep quietly all night.

I am also learning how to wait before rushing outside…I’m just so excited and want to chase all the squirrels!  Or I have the zoomies with my foster sister who has helped me be more confident.  I’d love to have a doggie sister or brother in my forever home to snuggle with us on the couch. Based on the things I am training on right now, an apartment may not be my ideal fit. 

Jade is about 1-2 years old and 30lbs. Since we don't know at all what doggy genes are in the dogs make up (we don't know who mom and dad are!), we are just guessing on breed and size when grown. 

All dogs have had a vet exam, are up to date on vaccinations, have been given a dewormer, treated for fleas and given heartworm preventative.  Dogs over 7 months have been heartworm tested.  

Please note that because we require a home visit at the time of adoption we can only place animals in homes within a 60 mile radius of Minneapolis. If you are interested in meeting this dog please fill out the pre-adoption application on our website at http://www.safehandsrescue.org under Adopt and we will get back to you to arrange a meeting in the foster home.

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in dog who needs a new home. Adoption can be one of the most fulfilling experiences in your life and especially in the life of your new canine companion.

A note to those looking at CPR. We have no perfect dogs - but many of our dogs have proven to be perfect for a certain someone. Our job is to find those someone's. Our most successful adopters come to CPR not because they want a dog. They come to us because they want to give a dog a home. We urge all of our potential adopters not to fall in love with a picture. While we like to know what you like in looks, a dog is more than a pretty face. Our goal is to match you with the best possible pet for you and your home. We want to create furever families.

Our descriptions contain all that we know about this dog today. We'll update as more information is known.

Are you looking to adopt within the next 30 days? If so please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and complete the application. You'll find it in the menu on the left hand side. You'll also find a total listing of all our dogs available.

Just browsing but interested in poodles and poodle mixes? Please drop a note to applications@carolinapoodlerescue.org with your name, address and phone # and email. We'll add you to our mailing list.

thanks
the CPR Adoption team

Date into Rescue: 10/15/2020
Reason for being in rescue: Peluche was surrendered by his owners to a shelter in North Carolina. Carolina Poodle Rescue pulled him from the shelter.
Foster location: Foster Home in Asheville, NC
Special Needs? Peluche is a senior dog with senior dog aches and pains. He had a major dental on 11/10/20 and lost 24 teeth! He has lower cervical spinal disease and is currently receiving laser treatments to help with pain management. Peluche has a 3/6 heart murmor. He is vision impaired. He has clearly had ear challenges. Peluche's previous owners noted that he has had bad reactions to sedation, resulting in seizing and labored breathing.
Weight: 8 lbs
Height: 6 in
Spayed/Neutered: Yes

Adoption Fee: $1 - I am priceless

Fence needed? No

What kind of home would be best for me? Peluche is a senior dog looking for a retirement home. He needs a quiet home that will be okay with a low energy dog. Peluche does have medical challenges as described and needs an owner experienced with senior dog care. He is not for a first time dog owner. Given his aches and pains we do not recommend Peluche for a home with children. Peluche will be happy living with other dogs and cats or as the only pet.

What is my personality like? Peluche is a sweet old man looking for his retirement home. He enjoys the simple things in life like slow days, long naps and sunbathing under warm blue skies. Peluche enjoys exploring our fenced property at the rescue and hanging out with his buddies. He is good with dogs of all sizes and totally indifferent to cats.

As noted above, Peluche has a number of medical challenges. The loss of 24 teeth during his recent dental means it's canned food for this boy. And boy does he love it! When Peluche wakes up from a nap he will cry from pain because he is stiff. Like humans, he needs to move and stretch out his back and neck muscles. Laser therapy is helping with this.

Peluche is a wonderful boy. He loves people and loves life (even when it is hard). We know there is a retirement home out there just looking for a precious angel to fill it!

How do I act when I first meet new people? Friendly

Other tips and tidbits: Peluche's estimated birthday is 0/15/2008

House trained? Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained. A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours. We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

Please note - we do not ship dogs. If you are interested in adopting, please take a look at the distance between the foster home location and your location and make sure you are willing to make that trip. Most of our dogs are at our farm in Pacolet, South Carolina.

To apply, please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and visit the tab on the left that directions you to the online application.

Please note that when screening applications, we look at the entire home and then make suggestions based on what would be a good fit for your home. You are not being screened for a specific dog although we are looking to see what type of dog interests you - poodles or non poodles, color, age, etc. Others here may be a better fit for you. It is very difficult to get to know a living animal from a picture and a short description. Since we are constantly getting in new dogs, this may be a dog not in our listings yet. We want you to be very happy with your new companion and will make suggestions based on what you tell us about you.

Thank you for considering CPR.

animal.description:
CHECK OUT OUR RECENT FOSTER GRADUATE!


Peppa is one of our most recent canine Foster Graduates--unlike our typical foster graduates, this little lady is going to remain in foster care until adoption as a part of our Adoption Ambassador program! Peppa's foster family has been very kind in not only keeping Peppa in foster care as she needed, but also to share photos and words of the times that were shared between them, in hopes to find her a home! 


"[Peppa] is wonderful! She minds extremely well, will come when called immediately, is completely potty trained and will not make a mess in the house. She won't steal food from your plate, or get in the trash and is generally very well behaved. She does well with cats, dogs, and horses and will very sweetly approach slowly because she wants to just hang out and be their friend. She gets along great with other dogs in particular and is very playful but if they aren't into it, will back off and be reserved. 


[Peppa] is absolutely the biggest cuddle monster and wants to be held and to sleep in people's lap. She is a bit dramatic and silly and will flop on the floor and pout if she doesn't get enough attention. She likes to 'talk' and will make howling/grunt noises that sound like a baby babbling and she will have long conversations with herself. She is very energetic despite her limp and enjoys going on long walks and playing with her toys. She is good off leash, even in a forest with a lot of smells and sounds, and will stay by your side and walk along well. 

Despite being energetic she can be low key and relax as long as there is a comfy bed or the promise of a cuddle. She sleeps in the weirdest positions and loves to bask in the sunshine and is a great dog, loving to lay on the porch. She is absolutely the best dog and would make a great companion for anyone.
--
Interested in adopting? Contact foster@southernpinesanimalshelter.org for more information on how to schedule a meet-'n'-greet or become one of our Adoption Ambassadors for a pet in need!
---
Peppa is a 1 year old female Shepherd/Catahoula Leopard Dog Mix. She weighs about 43 lbs. And is HEARTWORM POSITIVE. Her adoption fee is $0. To learn more about how our variable adoption fees are saving more lives than ever before, please visit: http://bit.do/SPAS_Adopt
---
*Regular adoption policies and procedures apply

animal.description:
Hi. My name is Belle. 
  I was rescued by my friends at HARP(Humane Animal Rescue Project). Before I met them, I lived in a horrible home with lots of drugs and scary people. My previous owner died and left me behind. Some very friendly ladies found me, gave me delicious food, a warm bed and blanket , and a safe place to stay. 
  The experience that HARP has with traumatized dogs has given me the confidence I need to begin learning not to fear the outside world.  HARP says that I should be adopted to a family with dog experience.
  Sometimes people make me nervous. Calm and structured homes suit me best. Children scare me. Some dogs scare me and others not so much. But a soft voice, kind touch and inviting smile will brighten my day. 
  Once I like you, there is nothing you can do to stop me from loving you. I'm one of the most special dogs in the world if you will give me a chance. I will fill your heart with love.
  -Belle
For more information and an adoption application contact Alfred:

animal.description:
Introducing Roxie the rockstar! This 70-pound tricolor hound mix is 6 years old, is house-trained and good on the leash. She prefers women, and loves to snuggle with her human friends. Roxie gets along with other dogs, but would prefer to be the only animal in the home. She would do best in a calm, quiet home without cats or small children. Roxie is a big goofball, and loves to play and run zoomies with her tennis ball. She experiences anxiety during storms and when she's left alone. Roxie is looking for a attentive, confident human who can give her the life she deserves. Contact Pet Helpers at 843-795-1110 to meet Miss Roxie!

Roxie's foster says, "She's a true Southern Belle -- sweet and gentle, has a smile and a nice hello for everyone she meets. Loves to be social and charms everyone she meets. Very polite and gentle with two legged and four legged strangers -- no jumping, no barking, no crowding. She doesn't beg -- moves away from the table when you sit down without you having to say anything. She has no guarding issues for food or toys. You can leave her alone and she's fine. She likes to watch the world go by from her perch or watch TV. But like every southern belle she has one bad habit -- not whiskey in her teacup or gossiping about the neighbors -- she hogs the couch! I cannot understand how she can still be in the shelter. She is an absolute peach of a dog!"

animal.description:
MEET SAINT!!

Sweet Saint is an adorable brindle 3 year old Labrador mix. He is affectionate, kind, silly, and LOVES to cuddle and play. He hasn't stopped smiling since he was picked up from the shelter. Just take a look at his sweet smile! Every day he will show you how thankful he is to be given a second chance.

Saint is a moderate-to-high energy level pup and at times can get a little rowdy during play with other dogs. However, he listens to corrections and commands extremely well. He is potty trained and very gentle with toys, bones, and food. He is great at sharing with his other doggy siblings too! Saint was found as a stray, so it is unknown how he is with cats or small children. He does exceptionally well with dogs his size or bigger though.
Saint would love to go for hikes, runs or car rides. He would make a great cuddle buddy and would be open for any adventures that come his way!

Due to Saint's unpleasant experience at the shelter, he is working through crate training and separation anxiety. Because of this, he would probably do best with a family who has someone home with him most the day. He would NOT do well being left alone in his kennel all day. But, who would? Saint loves his people. He loves them so much, he just wants to be with them as much as possible.

Saint is an amazing dog and his name could not be a better representation of who he is. He is truly an angel and will bring endless joy and laughter to your life. He deserves a companion or family that have their arms wide open and will love him as much as he will love them. If Saint sounds like a good addition to your family, fill out an application and fall in love with this sweet boy.

If you are interested in Saint, please email info@underdogaz.com or visit our site for our application www.underdogaz.com

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in dog who needs a new home. Adoption can be one of the most fulfilling experiences in your life and especially in the life of your new canine companion.

A note to those looking at CPR. We have no perfect dogs - but many of our dogs have proven to be perfect for a certain someone. Our job is to find those someone's. Our most successful adopters come to CPR not because they want a dog. They come to us because they want to give a dog a home. We urge all of our potential adopters not to fall in love with a picture. While we like to know what you like in looks, a dog is more than a pretty face. Our goal is to match you with the best possible pet for you and your home. We want to create furever families.

Our descriptions contain all that we know about this dog today. We'll update as more information is known.

Are you looking to adopt within the next 30 days? If so please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and complete the application. You'll find it in the menu on the left hand side. You'll also find a total listing of all our dogs available.

Just browsing but interested in poodles and poodle mixes? Please drop a note to applications@carolinapoodlerescue.org with your name, address and phone # and email. We'll add you to our mailing list.

thanks
the CPR Adoption team

Date into Rescue: 10/25/2018
Reason for being in rescue: Cherry was surrendered by her owners to a local animal shelter. CPR pulled her from the shelter.
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Special Needs? Cherry is spayed and UTD on all vaccines. She had a dental polishing on 8/28/20. At 16 pounds, Cherry is overweight and needs to lose about 3 pounds. She is vision impaired due to mature cataracts in both eyes.
Weight: 16 lbs - Cherry needs to lose at least 3 pounds to get back to a healthy weight.
Height: 9 in
Spayed/Neutered: Yes

Adoption Fee: $200

Fence needed? No

What kind of home would be best for me? Cherry is a quiet senior girl. She is vision impaired. Given this, a home with few to no stairs would be best for her. Cherry would love another senior dog in her forever home. She spends her days in rescue snuggled up with her best friend Cookie. We believe the warmth and companionship is comforting to her. Cherry is completely indifferent to cats. She would love to be a quiet retiree's beloved companion!

What is my personality like? Cherry is a sweet senior girl. She prefers to spend most of her days sleeping. She gets along well with other dogs and loves to cuddle with them. Most days find Cherry snuggled up in a bed with another quiet, senior dog. Cherry walks well on a leash and will follow your voice. She isn't up for long, rigorous walks, but enjoys the warmth of sunshine on her back. Cherry is a wonderful dog for grooming.

Cherry is a simple girl looking for a retirement home. A warm bed, another dog to snuggle with, and lots of lap time is all it takes to make this princess happy!

How do I act when I first meet new people? Friendly

Other tips and tidbits: Cherry's estimated birthday is 10/23/2010

House trained? Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained. A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours. We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

Please note - we do not ship dogs. If you are interested in adopting, please take a look at the distance between the foster home location and your location and make sure you are willing to make that trip. Most of our dogs are at our farm in Pacolet, South Carolina.

To apply, please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and visit the tab on the left that directions you to the online application.

Please note that when screening applications, we look at the entire home and then make suggestions based on what would be a good fit for your home. You are not being screened for a specific dog although we are looking to see what type of dog interests you - poodles or non poodles, color, age, etc. Others here may be a better fit for you. It is very difficult to get to know a living animal from a picture and a short description. Since we are constantly getting in new dogs, this may be a dog not in our listings yet. We want you to be very happy with your new companion and will make suggestions based on what you tell us about you.

Thank you for considering CPR.

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in dog who needs a new home. Adoption can be one of the most fulfilling experiences in your life and especially in the life of your new canine companion.

A note to those looking at CPR. We have no perfect dogs - but many of our dogs have proven to be perfect for a certain someone. Our job is to find those someone's. Our most successful adopters come to CPR not because they want a dog. They come to us because they want to give a dog a home. We urge all of our potential adopters not to fall in love with a picture. While we like to know what you like in looks, a dog is more than a pretty face. Our goal is to match you with the best possible pet for you and your home. We want to create furever families.

Our descriptions contain all that we know about this dog today. We'll update as more information is known.

Are you looking to adopt within the next 30 days? If so please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and complete the application. You'll find it in the menu on the left hand side. You'll also find a total listing of all our dogs available.

Just browsing but interested in poodles and poodle mixes? Please drop a note to applications@carolinapoodlerescue.org with your name, address and phone # and email. We'll add you to our mailing list.

thanks
the CPR Adoption team

Date into Rescue: 8/24/2020
Reason for being in rescue: Lowrider was found as a stray by a volunteer
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Special Needs? Lowrider has weak hind legs. His back sustained an injury, likely sacroccylgeal, which is causing ataxia and knuckling and loss of continence. This injury cannot be readily identified on radiographs, though we can provide radiographs. Per our vet, not much can be done other than strengthening exercises. Lowrider was neutered and had a dental on 11/3/20.
Weight: 19 lbs
Height: 14 in
Spayed/Neutered: Yes

Adoption Fee: $1 - I am special

Fence needed? No

What kind of home would be best for me? Lowrider is a special boy looking for a special home. His back legs have limited mobility. This doesn't stop him for running slowly in wide open fields and living his best life. Given this, Lowrider needs a home where there are no stairs and lots of soft surfaces. His legs will rub raw if he drags them too much, particularly on hard surfaces. Belly Bands will be a must in Lowrider's forever home. He does have some incontinence and leaks urine.

Lowrider will be best as an only dog with a family that understands dogs with special needs. He could live happily with cats. He would love children as well. Lowrider does not need a fenced yard. He would love to go for strolls in a stroller. Lowrider is a poster child for living your best life despite the cards life deals you!

What is my personality like? Lowrider is a special boy. We don't know what life for Lowrider was like prior to being found by a volunteer, but it involved an injury. At some point in his history Lowrider sustained a significant back injury which is causing ataxia and knuckling in his rear legs and incontinence. Unfortunately there is not a lot that can be done other than strengthening exercises. It is highly doubtful Lowrider will ever recover full mobility in his hind legs.

Despite his physical limitations, Lowrider is a happy boy who is full of personality. He is a sweet boy who loves sunbathing, belly rubs, and being where people are. Lowrider is living in a cottage with other dogs, but can be selective about who he likes. Lower mobility does not slow this boy down if he doesn't want someone in his space. Lowrider will urinate when he gets excited, including if you pick him up. Just be aware when you go to give him snuggles!

How do I act when I first meet new people? Friendly

Other tips and tidbits: Lowrider's estimated birthday is 8/24/2013. This is a complete estimate based on his overall condition. We have no history on Lowrider so his birthday is purely an educated guess.

House trained? Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained. A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours. We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

Please note - we do not ship dogs. If you are interested in adopting, please take a look at the distance between the foster home location and your location and make sure you are willing to make that trip. Most of our dogs are at our farm in Pacolet, South Carolina.

To apply, please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and visit the tab on the left that directions you to the online application.

Please note that when screening applications, we look at the entire home and then make suggestions based on what would be a good fit for your home. You are not being screened for a specific dog although we are looking to see what type of dog interests you - poodles or non poodles, color, age, etc. Others here may be a better fit for you. It is very difficult to get to know a living animal from a picture and a short description. Since we are constantly getting in new dogs, this may be a dog not in our listings yet. We want you to be very happy with your new companion and will make suggestions based on what you tell us about you.

Thank you for considering CPR.
animal.name: Lowrider - A Special Boy!

Angel was a breeding dog. She had three owners before coming to us. She was spayed & the vet clinic did not tie off multiple spots. She was bleeding internally.  She was rushed to medvet to save her life.  

She is 8 years old. Shes an American Bully. Shes 50 lbs. She needs kept extremely lean due to arthritis. She was shot at one point in her life. She's full of buck shot. She is very sweet. She just wants to lay with you. She will give kisses. The end of her tongue sticks out. She is slow due to arthritis. She is great with older children. She did snap at a 2 year old over a dpg toy. She barely broke skin. She is crate trained and house trained. But needs let out often.  She has mammary tumors. She has surgery scheduled November 23rd to remove them. She'll need another surgery as its too much to do at once. She will start heartworm treatment after her surgeries. She's had a 6 month proheart and doxycycline to prepare for treatment.  Shes had numerous exams. She had a negative fecal. She has arthritis in her elbow. She takes rimadyl and probiotocs daily. She does have food allergies.  
She would love a calm foster or forever home. She's located in New Orleans LA

animal.description:
Brady was rescued off the streets of Bosnia in 2017 and has been living in Virginia since being rescued by our organization that same year. Due to unexpected changes in his previous owners' health and living situation, Brady was relinquished back to our organization. 

Brady is a sweet chunker who loves chasing his ball and going for walks. Brady is very passive with both male and female dogs and does not show alpha tendencies. He is very strong and can be a bit powerful and pulls when on a leash when he sees someone unfamiliar or another dog/wildlife but shows the ability to be corrected so a family with a strong pack leader would be best. He does not bark much but when he does it is a very high pitched bark. 

He has had recurrent issues with his skin which appears to be dry skin/dandruff. He has been on steroids in the past and medicated shampoo treatments, and the steroids have contributed to him being overweight. His weight can be mitigated with adequate and regular exercise - he has been going on daily walks with his foster family and is losing weight. 

He gets along with most other dogs after being properly introduced and integrated. His breed mix is unknown. Brady turned 4 years old in October 2020. He is over 50 lbs with a medium build. His new home should have a large contained area to run and play. Brady has not been cat tested. His previous home did include other dogs including Lola, his packmate who was also relinquished.  Please view our other postings to see Lola. Brady is currently being fostered near Charlottesville, VA. 

We are a registered 501c3 nonprofit. Learn more at http://www.thetanzieproject.org

animal.description:
Beverly is approximately 4 years old and 9lbs. She needs someone willing to take the time with her to trust people. We believe she was abused and she was not socialized properly. Beverly is very cuddly once she gets to know you. She's startled by sudden movement or loud noises so we assume children wpuldnt be a good fit. She needs a home with a secure yard since she is nervous. Beverly is house and crate trained. She's best with dogs her own size but okay with larger calm dogs as well. 

Beverly is currently on Prozac due to her nervousness. She has allergies to chicken and needs a low protein food so she doesn't have urinary issues. She's currently eating natural balance duck. She has a low grade luxating patella that doesn't bother her but needs to be on joint supplements for life for this condition. Beverly has heartworms. She has received a 6 month pro heart injection and finished doxycycline. She will soon begin heartworm treatment which will we cover. After treatment she needs a dental to remove some crooked teeth which we will also cover. Beverly is up to date on shots, flea prevention. She is spayed and microchipped. She had a negative fecal and great exam. She is located in New Orleans LA

animal.description:
Ziggy is a Chihuahua and Jack Russell mix which is certainly an odd mix!  They said he is ten years old but he doesn’t act his age at all. He acts much younger and maybe we should name him ZIPPY!  He was surrendered because he loves females but not males so we are looking for a female only home. Ziggy cannot even be in a home where there is a male anywhere. Not sure what happened to him but he sure does love the women.

 Ziggy weighs six pounds but he is more like 60 pounds of love!  Such a good boy!  He loves to curl up right next to you or in your lap yet he is playful and excited at times.  Ziggy is very trainable as he loves food and can eat eat eat!  He has so much spunk and personality. We haven’t seen any food or toy aggression and he’s not a barker which is always a nice characteristic.  He currently uses a doggy door to go outside to do his business and he learned that super quick! 

 If you are wanting a companion to love and who enjoys being loved and you are a female, Ziggy is your dog!  Email storkwoods@comcast.net for an adoption application which is the best way to begin a potential adoption.

We have fosters in several areas of the country. Ziggy is being fostered in TN.

animal.description: Hello! Im Bambi. Frankly, Ive had a hard life until now, and Im only two in hooman years. The shelter has helped me so much. They actually saved my life! Id been homeless and starved, got heartworms, and was hit by a car. Animal Protection rescued me. The hoomans at the shelter made me well, and the hoomans in the county gave money to pay. My tail wags for you all! Thats mostly past me now. Ive gained weight. The food here is so good to me, and I get fed EVERY DAY! My heartworms will be taken care of soon. My injuries have almost totally healed. Whats next I hope -- is a home and my own peeple who will be patient and kind. They will help me learn that not all hoomans are bad. I grew to love the shelter hoomans, but am shy around new peeple. You will be new peeple to me when we meet. With a little time, Ill come out of my shell with you, too, and love you forever. Im a sweet, gentle girl. I dont understand why hoomans didnt know that before. Youll see my sweetness when we go home together. I dont remember living in a real home before. Will you help me learn how? Having a safe place thats mine alone would be wonderful. The shelter hoomans say a crate will help me blend with the family. I can sleep there, eat there, and get toys and treats there. That sounds so good to me. I hope you make a date to meet me. Fill out the advance adoption form and ask to meet Bambi. I will become your best friend forever.

animal.description:
Do you love the look of a Boxer but really prefer a smaller, more portable dog? Then Casper might just be the guy for you! He is basically a giant Chihuahua but looks like a miniature Boxer. Casper has an extremely expressive face and has a type of permanent look of skepticism mixed with genuine concern. ""Are you really going to eat another potato chip and not share it with me? Hmmmm."" 

Casper is great with other dogs and has lived in a foster home with lots of other little dogs like himself. He also does well with cats. He's a very sweet and sensitive guy that would do best with an experienced dog owner. Casper has the tendancy to nip those who are unwelcome in his space, specifically people who he is not familiar with and who approach him uninvited. I mean, don't we all hate that?! 6 feet apart, people, please! Casper is a big snuggler and would love to curl up next to you and watch your favorite show (More True Crime? He won't complain!) and help you unwind at the end of the day. 

Casper enjoys walks and excercise just as much as the next dog but is also flexible and won't hold you to a strict schedule. Sometimes plans change and a car ride will do the trick! 

If you'd like to meet Casper or speak with his foster mom, please fill out an application at celestialzoo.org, and she can get you more details and set up a meet-and-greet!

animal.description:
Purebred rottweiler. Good with people, great temperament, well mannered and friendly. Good with some dogs. He came to us with Sara and Boo. All three dog were locked in their home for approximately 10 days with no food or water with their owner who had passed away. They were all laying by her body when the police finally came to do a wellness check. Very loyal dogs, and very protective of their property but they just put on a good act. Once you let them out of their house, they are are very friendly. We will be getting his teeth cleaned and seen by our vet soon. 
if you would like to adopt maverick here is Our Adoption Process... If you are interested in adopting one of our fun loving not so rotten rotties, you will be asked to fill out a questionnaire that will allows us to get to know you better and to make sure the dog you are looking at is a good fit for your family and lifestyle. You can access our questionnaire by going to our website, www.rottenrottie.com click on the forms tab, and fill out the questionnaire and submit it online. After we review your answers, if we feel that the dog that you are interested in, is not a good fit for you and your family, we may recommend a different rottweiler companion. After we determine which Rottweiler(s) is the best for you, we will set up a time so that you can meet him or her at their house, where they will feel most comfortable and act as they normally do. An adoption contract will be signed to finalize the adoption and we do ask for a rehoming fee of $400 for most adults, $250 for most of our seniors 6 years and above for any rottweiler mix of any age (except puppies) . Our fees for puppies fluctuate depending on how much we had to invest into them or their litter, and weather they are purebred or a mix. These funds are necessary so that our organization may continue to rehome rottweilers. ALL of our dogs are sterilized, fully vaccinated and microchipped, heartworm tested negative and come with a collar and a leash. We have also addressed any injury or illness that they had when they came to us, or received in foster care. These problems will be disclosed to the adopter prior to adoption.

animal.description:
Meet Frito - a handsome 2 1/2 year old, 60lb Pit mix. He is very sweet and cuddly, especially in the morning. Frito is crate trained but sleeps in his human's bed at night, often snoring during his peaceful dreams. He prefers to be close to his humans as much as possible and loves to follow them from room to room throughout the day, unless he is napping on the couch.

He's a good boy who knows all his basic commands - sit, lay down, roll over, give paw, other paw, wait, come and crate. He's still working on down, especially when he's overly excited. He walks well on a leash/harness but could use some additional training in his forever home since he can get distracted by other walkers or dogs. Frito loves to chew on his bones and chew toys, occasionally "galloping" through the house with his favorite toy in his mouth.

We would love to see him in a home with someone who will provide lots of snuggles, praise and love. Since he's not a fan of his crate, we'd prefer if his forever home used it only on a limited basis or not at all. A house without children is preferred and a fenced in backyard is a plus. Frito is EXTREMELY smart and eager to learn and please his people. He would benefit from an experienced dog owner who would be able to commit to teach him the additional skills he needs.

Frito's adoption fee is $300. Check out rescuedohio.org to apply and become an approved adopter!

animal.description:
Lily is a sweet, 9 yr old blond Pekingese who weighs 16lbs. Lily was surrendered to us by her owners who were moving,

Like most Pekes, you need to go slowly with Lily until she gets to know you. She loves to have her belly rubbed, sleep under your desk while you are working and snuggle with you on the couch during TV time. She will follow you all over the house and happily sleep in her bed at the foot of your bed. Lily is very social with her family and loves to be with her people, so she needs a home where her family is not gone all day.  
 
Lily is simply adorable and has several Peke traits, so she would do best with someone familiar with the breed. Lily can be bossy, especially when she meets new dogs, so she needs to be an only dog.

Lily requires an all adult home with a small, securely fenced yard. She is not a candidate for a home with children. Lily is housetrained and doesn’t even mind going outside to potty when it is raining.  
 
The adoption range for this dog is limited to NC, SC and VA.

If you are interested in adopting this dog, contact h2hadoptions@gmail.com. An all adult home with a fenced yard (fence must be attached to the home) is required to adopt from Hart-2-Heart Rescue.

There is an application process and adoption fee. We are an all-volunteer organization, and in addition to saving dogs, we have other responsibilities, so we appreciate your patience and understanding during this process. Response time can take up to 5 business days.

Please inquire only if you are willing to come to Greensboro, North Carolina to meet the dog after we schedule your home visit. We do not ship dogs or put them on transports. Adoption fee is $400.

Veterinary Care: All Hart-2-Heart Rescue foster dogs are spayed/neutered, current on heartworm prevention, parvo/distemper, bordetella, and rabies vaccines and are professionally groomed. As needed, our foster dogs have teeth cleanings, extractions, bloodwork and other diagnostic testing.

animal.description:
Meet Benson! 
This handsome
boy is about 3.5 years old and 70 lbs of love! Benson loves nothing more than to feel safe and snuggle on the couch or lounge around with his humans. He is very sweet and gives a lot of love! Benson is great with humans (kids 10+ ok too) and loves to meet new people. He’s very smart and quick to learn new tricks like high five, paw, stay, sit and lay. He’s also crate and potty trained! Benson was not properly trained or introduced to other animals early on in his life, so he will do better in a home where he can be the only pet. The ideal home for him would be a home with a fenced in yard and a family who wants just one dog. 
Benson has learned a communication system built on rewards and positive verbal markers. This system can be used to continue to develop and nurture his self confidence. Much of his dog reactivity is rooted in a lack of feeling safe. To thrive he will need a strong leader to advocate for him, manage his occasional outbursts of leash reactivity (towards cats/dogs) and to protect him from harm. His ideal match is someone mentally alert enough and physically strong enough to correct and redirect him when he fails to control his impulses. He enjoys affection and praise which can be used as a form of reward. He is crate trained which can be used at times when he must be left alone. He has shown no signs of human aggression or resource guarding but he seems to have had previous success grabbing the leash away from his handler when overstimulated or
frustrated. Another reason a muzzle is ideal for leash walking or being on leash in public.  He is not for someone looking for a running or walking partner, or someone that wants to take their dog out to the breweries. He is a sweet human bonded dog that wants to be by your side at home, and will reward you with lots of snuggles and kisses. Benson's trainer has graciously offered to help any potential adopter with transitioning Benson into his new home and provide support. Benson has had a tremendously difficult life but he is ready to find love and support in a family who loves him. Benson was rescued
from a shelter in Los Angeles, CA and is being fostered in Eugene, OR. Will you be his hero? 

 If you are interested in Benson, please fill out an application at
www.streetdoghero.org/forms

animal.description:
Coltrane is a very handsome 2-3 year old Self Red merle Australian Shepherd with a full tail, located in Fayetteville, North Carolina. 
He is UTD on all vaccinations, neutered, current on Heartworm/Flea tick prevention and is microchipped.

He needs a fully fenced yard, No children under 10 years of age, No male dogs, and No cats or small animals in the home.

If you are looking for an active boy that still enjoys couch snuggles in the evenings, Coltrane is the best of both worlds. 
Even though he weighs in at 50 lbs, he sees no reason why he can't be a lap dog.
He is a cuddle buddy for sure!
He is fully house and crate trained. 
We have been working on basic obedience which he has picked up on quickly and he is very food motivated.
He walks well on leash but will still pull occasionally when he gets overly excited. 
He is a handsome boy that is absolutely full of personality.
He loves to shake paws and give high fives for treats or when he's asking for belly rubs. Belly rubs are his very favorite!!!
He has the classic velcro Aussie personality and will be your shadow for life. He also has absolutely no sense of what privacy is because he will happily follow you into the bathroom without any hesitation.
He loves toys and definitely has ball drive.
He greatly enjoys going for car rides too.
Any children in the home will need to be 10 years of age or older, as small children make him very nervous.
Coltrane gets along great with female dogs but is overly dominant when interacting with male dogs. 
Due to this behavior any existing dogs in the home will have to be female.
He would do fine as an only dog too though.
He also has an extremely high prey drive so cats and other small animals are a no for him.
With his dominance level towards male dogs and the high prey drive, off leash exercise in unfenced environments and dog park settings would be dangerous, so a fully fenced yard is a requirement so he has a safe place to run and burn off energy. 
Preferably 6 ft. high as he is very capable and will try to jump the fence if given the opportunity.

Due to this anyone considering adopting him will also need to take into consideration that he will require ongoing STRICT supervision when outside.
Coltrane also has Coloboma/hyperplasia in his left eye.
This is a birth defect to the iris in his left eye which allows for too much light to enter the cornea resulting in light sensitivity. 
To help with the sensitivity to light we have been working hard on conditioning him to comfortably wear Rex Specs goggles when outside. 
He is doing really great with them.
The goggles are a must for both his comfort and his eye health, as protection from sunlight will help to prevent early development of cataracts.
Added bonus is he looks super cool wearing them.

If you think Coltrane is a good fit for your family, please fill out our application:

animal.description:
Hello Robyn here. Do you love brown-eyed girls? Or maybe you prefer blue-eyed ladies? 
Well, with me you get both! I know, you are thinking, "how can it be so?!" Well, just look at my gorgeous photos and you will see my adorable face and those fanciful eyes! And you know what else? I'm just as beautiful on the inside and as the outside. No really, foster mommy told me so. I am super sweet, lovable, friendly, and well-mannered; all the things that make me a perfect pup. And Foster mommy says I am the best pup she has had this year which says a lot considering everything the humans have had to endure in 2020. But for me, 2020 has been filled with angels, K-9 Angels. 

As for me, the K-9 Angels have taught me so much, and now I am ready to get settled into a forever home. I would love a family who enjoys giving belly rubs and letting have a few squeaky toys to play with. Oh, and some stuffed animals, too, because I do enjoy pulling out the stuffing. Do you have a spare tennis ball around your house? Well, if you throw it I would love to play fetch with you. I am still learning how to play with other dogs at the park. I have so much fun playing chase with them and getting to know them, and who will and won't share their frisbees and balls. Some dogs can be a little bossy when it comes to their stuff, and foster mommy is showing me how to ignore those types and help me focus my energy on being a happy go lucky girl.

My foster mommy and I go for long walks along the bayou, exploring the great outdoors. She's teaching me to walk slow and in control, and not to forge ahead at full speed. With basic commands, I am able to understand what being a good dog is on leash. Oh, and those treats she keeps in her pocket help let me know I am doing a good job.

And speaking of training, my foster mommy has taught me to sit and wait to be called for mealtime. I am such a smart pup. My favorite time of the day is snuggle time. Foster mama let's me snuggle with her on the couch and we watch TV together. Her head makes a perfect pillow. She says I snore so cutely, but I've never heard it so I think she is lying. 

So now that you are totally in love with me and are frantically working on your application, here are a few details to think about: I am good with dogs that are willing to share toys and are not an alpha female. I can play a little rough with big dogs like me (though I am learning how to be gentler) and it might be best if I am in a house with dogs who won't mind a little rough housing. As for cats, I am very curious about the ones I've seen around the neighborhood but don't have any experience one on one with them. I haven't been around kids but we could schedule a meet up and see how things go!

So get your application filled out, because I know I am going to be pretty popular after all the families out there read my impressive bio. Oh, and by the way, I am totally housetrained. 

Robyn is a female Shepherd/Black Mouth Cur mix who weighs 46 lbs and was born 10/3/2018.

Lorelei is a 2-year-old brindle beauty with sweet, expressive eyes who came to us from our rescue partners in Tennessee with her 6 puppies (who were quickly adopted out). She was found as a stray and likely had a difficult past that is apparent in her distrust of people in general, but especially men. 

Lorelei is very high energy and loves to spend her time playing with any animal that will run and wrestle with her. She likes other dogs but can be very dominant so would do best with more submissive doggie friends. Surprisingly enough, she is very sweet to cats, but is not a fan of children so would need to go to a home without children. 

She is a sweet girl who needs a chance to see that life and people can be pretty nice. Once she feels comfortable with you, she is a very cuddly and affectionate dog. She would love an active family that will take her on adventures during the day then settle on the couch for snuggles at night! She is an angel in her crate and catches onto commands quickly. If you would like to meet Lorelei, please fill out a survey today at https://www.playersforpits.com/adoption-survey

animal.description:
THEY ARE A BONDED PAIR & MUST BE ADOPTED TOGETHER - They have been available for 2 months with little interest due to being a bonded pair. These two are very easy going and chill. It can be intimidating to adopt 2 dogs at the same time but with these 2 you wouldn't even notice! 

YOU CAN FOLLOW THEM ON IG: 
Kali_n_Cruz_BondedPair

Their Story:
Cruz was adopted from our rescue 3 years ago and his adoptive family returned him due to them going through a separation recently and neither could keep him or his sister (Kali). They were going to send her to the shelter and we weren't going to let the happen since these two are inseparable as you can see in the pictures! They had 2 other siblings, 1 large sister and 1 small sister which were kept by family members. They get along with all other size dogs as long as introduced properly. 

Meet this dynamic duo, Cruz & Kali!! They are the absolute sweetest and loving dogs you could meet. 

Cruz is a male brindle pittie mix.  He's about 4-5 years old and is a medium size dog weighing approx. 40-50 lbs. He is timid at first but will warm right up once he realizes he'll get attention. 

Kali is a female white & grey pittie/possible bulldog mix. She's about 8-10 years old and is a large dog weighing approx. 90-100 lbs. Kali follows Cruz everywhere, she's like the little big sister. 

They love cuddling up with each other or with their humans. They are inside dogs only, they don't like being out in the cold (only to potty). They really like to hang out with their humans so they'd like to go to a home where they will spend a lot of time with their family but if needed can go in a kennel when nobody is home. They both like to play with their toys and run around. These two really like attention, especially Cruz, he will always try to get some lovin'.  They also like to go on walks. 

If you're interested in getting more information, pictures, or meeting these 2 squishy faces please email us at findingabestfriend@gmail.com or you can text their foster mom directly at 209-298-2433. They are located in Stockton. 

Any current animal in the home must be altered and up to date on vaccines. 

If you meet these two you'll fall right in love! 

Thank you for your interest!

Baxter's at that perfect age where he still has lots of energy to run and play. He loves to run, and go for rides in the car, and walks well on a leash, but he's also content to lay around and nap most of the day away.

Given Baxter's timid nature, he'll do best in a relatively quiet home (no small children). He gets along great with well-mannered cats

animal.description:
*Please read entire description prior to applying for Bianca*
Bianca would do best in a quiet neighborhood, outside of the city!
Bianca also known as B is looking for her forever home. This 8 year old Yorkie mix comes to us as an owner surrender meaning she is already leash trained, potty trained and has her own routines. Bianca responds to basic commands like stop, sit, and come, and loves to play with squeaky toys, especially balls (balls of all kind). While she is sweet and lovable 99% of the time, B does have a bite history according to her previous owners. We have witnessed her become aggressive with sudden gestures like opening doors, but she calms down after a moment or two. At that point we redirect her attention with treats (she is food motivated). 

For these reasons, we recommend an experienced adopter who lives alone and is patient with no kids or other pets at home. 

*Please note she has seen an animal behaviorist. 


Interested in becoming a forever home for Bianca? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Bianca.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Bianca the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  
For immediate consideration, please attach your application to the initial inquiry to help us expedite the process.

Our adoption fee is $475. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
Please read the bio in full for answers to your questions. In the event you have a question that is not covered in the bio, please email info@seniordoghaven.org. If interested in adopting, please complete an adoption application which can be found at www.seniordoghaven.org under the Adoption Process tab. Please note that because all of our dogs live in foster homes, we are unable to set up meetings with a dog unless we have a completed adoption application on file. Adoptions must be about an hour of Wilmington, DE in order for our volunteers to be able to conduct an in person home visit. 

Jack and Jill are 8 year old brother and sister siblings who originally came to us by way of a local SPCA where they were surrendered because their owner had too many dogs in the house.  They were not socialized at all and hid wherever possible when we first took them in so they have spent 5 months in a foster home learning how to trust.

These two have sure had their share of maladies while with us!    Both had extremely high white blood cell counts of unknown origin, which are now finally back to normal.  Both were also morbidly obese, Jack was over 20 pounds and Jill was over 18 pounds when they should be more like 10-12 pounds at most.   Because they seem to have a very low metabolism and gain weight on standard dog food, they have been on a strict home cooked diet for the past 4 months and are now down to 12 pounds (Jack) and 12.5 pounds (Jill).   Their new family will need to ensure that they are kept on a diet that will not cause them to gain weight.  Especially because Jack had a very high grade luxating patella on one of his back legs which required knee surgery and does have a mild luxating patella in the other back leg so any extra weight will be detrimental to his knee.    They have both been doing well on Hills Metabolic Support Food and Just Food For Dogs Metabolic support food so they don't necessarily need home cooked food any more now that they are at a more optimal weight. 

Jack and Jill are still on the shy side when you first meet them.    It will take them some time to warm up and trust people therefore we will be looking for a  quiet home for them without children who can be patient and give them the time that they need to adjust and trust.   Jack warms up much faster than Jill and will roll over for belly rubs quickly.  Jill, on the other hand, is much more scared and reserved.  They are so scared of the world outside of their foster home that they do not walk on leash or go outside of their back yard and probably never will so they will need a secure fenced in yard for potty breaks and a bit of exercise.  Speaking of potty breaks, neither Jack or Jill are fully housebroken and will need a family that can get them on a regular potty schedule and work with them on house training.  They do use pee pads in their foster home and Jack would much prefer to use pee pads and typically needs to be carried outside to do his business.   Both dogs need to be kept outside for enough time to do their business since they tend to run inside too quickly and end up using pee pads.  

Jill is extremely protective of Jack so we feel is it best for them to be the only dogs in the house.  Jill gets a little cranky towards Jack like siblings do and they do have short minor spats with each other.  We originally thought that maybe it would be best to separate them but neither do well without the other so we assume Jack is just so used to his sister telling him what to do, that he is lost without her.  

Both love sitting with their foster family at night and enjoying belly rubs.  They would love sleeping next to their family as well but haven’t been able to very much because of other dogs in the household.   Because they can’t get full one on one time with their foster family right because of other dogs in the household, we can’t wait for them to be able to enjoy their family all of the time!   
We know that we are asking a lot of a family for them, but we know they deserve it and we know that the perfect family is out there waiting for them!
